{"title_page": "Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u\n| image = \n| fullname = Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1997|07|08|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Medgidia]], Romania\n| height = 1.78m\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[CS Universitatea Craiova|Universitatea Craiova]]\n| clubnumber = 10\n| youthyears1 = 2010\u20132015\n| youthclubs1 = [[Gheorghe Hagi Football Academy|Gheorghe Hagi Academy]]\n| years1 = 2016\u20132018\n| clubs1 = [[FC Viitorul Constan\u021ba|Viitorul Constan\u021ba]]\n| caps1 = 42\n| goals1 = 1\n| years2 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs2 = [[CS Universitatea Craiova|Universitatea Craiova]]\n| caps2 = 60\n| goals2 = 14\n| nationalyears1 = 2015\u20132016\n| nationalteam1 = [[Romania national under-19 football team|Romania U19]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 6\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2017\u20132019\n| nationalteam2 = [[Romania national under-21 football team|Romania U21]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 13\n| nationalgoals2 = 2\n| nationalyears3 = 2018\u2013\n| nationalteam3 = [[Romania national football team|Romania]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 6\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| pcupdate = {{date|2020-01-31}}\n| ntupdate = {{date|2019-11-18}}\n}}\n\n'''Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u''' ({{IPA-ro|alek\u02c8sandru t\u0283ik\u0268l\u02c8d\u0259w}}; born 8 July 1997) is a Romanian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[CS Universitatea Craiova]] and the [[Romania national football team|Romania national team]].\n\nHe started his career at [[FC Viitorul Constan\u021ba|Viitorul Constan\u021ba]], recording his professional debut with the team in 2016. Two years later, he transferred to Universitatea Craiova.\n\nCic\u00e2ld\u0103u made his full international debut for [[Romania national football team|Romania]] in March 2018.\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Early years / Viitorul Constan\u021ba===\nCic\u00e2ld\u0103u was raised in [[Mircea Vod\u0103, Constan\u021ba|Satu Nou]], a village near [[Medgidia]], [[Constan\u021ba County]], and started playing football at the age of 8. He later joined the [[Gheorghe Hagi Football Academy|Gheorghe Hagi Academy]], which serves as the youth setup of [[FC Viitorul Constan\u021ba|Viitorul Constan\u021ba]].<ref name=\"GSP_interview\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/foto-exclusiv-cicaldau-a-parasit-cantonamentul-viitorului-si-vine-la-bucuresti-sa-semneze-cu-noua-echipa-543406.html|title=Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u a p\u0103r\u0103sit cantonamentul Viitorului \u0219i vine la Bucure\u0219ti s\u0103 semneze cu noua echip\u0103!|trans-title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u left Viitorul and is travelling to Bucharest to sign for a new team|newspaper=[[Gazeta Sporturilor]]|language=Romanian|date=5 July 2018|accessdate=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nCic\u00e2ld\u0103u made his debut in the [[Liga I|first division]] for Viitorul on 31 March 2016, aged 18, in a 1\u20131 away draw with [[ASA 2013 T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219|ASA T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digisport.ro/live-text/asa-tg-mures-viitorul-1-1-gazdele-au-salvat-un-punct-pe-final-eroare-uriasa-pecanha-300495|title=ASA Tg. Mure\u0219 - Viitorul 1-1|publisher=[[Digi Sport (Romania)|Digi Sport]]|language=Romanian|date=31 March 2016|accessdate=25 March 2018}}</ref> He became a regular starter for the club in the [[2017\u201318 Liga I|2017\u201318 season]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prosport.ro/video/fotbal-intern/nationala/interviu-video-da-la-inceput-eram-doar-un-pusti-promitator-ca-la-20-de-ani-fara-griji-dar-adulat-de-fani-cicaldau-vorbeste-despre-hagi-interesul-lui-becali-si-nationala-de-tineret-16814461|title=INTERVIU VIDEO &#124; \"Da! La \u00eenceput eram doar un pu\u015fti promi\u0163\u0103tor\". Ca la 20 de ani, f\u0103r\u0103 griji dar adulat de fani. Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u vorbe\u015fte despre Hagi, interesul lui Becali \u015fi na\u0163ionala de tineret|trans-title=VIDEO INTERVIEW &#124; \"Yes! At first I was just a promising youth.\" Like a 20-year-old, without worries but beloved by fans. Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u talks about Hagi, Becali's interest and the youth national team|publisher=[[ProSport]]|language=Romanian|date=10 November 2017|accessdate=25 March 2018}}</ref> amassing 38 appearances and one goal in all competitions.\n\n===Universitatea Craiova===\nOn 6 July 2018, Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u agreed to a four-year contract with [[CS Universitatea Craiova]], being assigned the [[Squad number (association football)|number 10 shirt]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ucv1948.ro/Alexandru-Cicaldau-jucatorul-Stiintei-pentru-4-ani|title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u, juc\u0103torul \u0218tiin\u021bei pentru 4 ani!|trans-title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u, the player of ''\u0218tiin\u021ba'' for the next 4 years!|publisher=CS Universitatea Craiova|language=Romanian|date=6 July 2018|accessdate=6 July 2018}}</ref> Press reported the fee at figures between [[Euro|\u20ac]]750,000 and \u20ac1 million plus interest on the capital gain of a potential future transfer.<ref name=\"GSP_interview\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sport.ro/liga-1/transfer-urias-in-liga-1-unul-dintre-cei-mai-doriti-jucatori-a-ales-o-pe-craiova-dupa-ce-a-refuzat-fcsb.html|title=Transfer URIAS in Liga 1! Unul dintre cei mai doriti jucatori a ales-o pe Craiova dupa ce a refuzat FCSB si CFR Cluj! Anuntul diminetii|trans-title=HUGE transfer in Liga 1! One of the most desired players chose Craiova after rejecting FCSB and CFR Cluj!|publisher=[[Sport.ro]]|language=Romanian|date=5 July 2018|accessdate=6 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/cati-bani-primeste-hagi-pentru-transferul-lui-cicaldau-suma-care-l-a-convins-pe-rege-sa-si-vanda-unul-dintre-cei-mai-buni-fotbalisti-la-craiova-17345369|title=C\u00e2\u0163i bani prime\u015fte Hagi pentru transferul lui Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u. Suma care l-a convins pe \"Rege\" s\u0103-\u015fi v\u00e2nd\u0103 unul dintre cei mai buni fotbali\u015fti la Craiova|trans-title=How much money Hagi receives for the transfer of Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u. The sum that convinced \"the King\" to sell one of his best footballers to Craiova|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian|date=6 July 2018|accessdate=6 July 2018}}</ref> He made his first appearance for \"the White-Blues\" eight days later in the [[2018 Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei|Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei]], playing the full match as [[CFR Cluj]] came victorious 1\u20130.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://frf.ro/competitii/competitii-masculin/cfr-cluj-a-castigat-supercupa-romaniei-2018-id24377.html|title=CFR Cluj a c\u00e2\u0219tigat Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei 2018|trans-title=CFR Cluj won the 2018 Romanian Supercup|publisher=[[Romanian Football Federation]]|language=Romanian|date=14 July 2018|accessdate=15 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180715011429/http://frf.ro/competitii/competitii-masculin/cfr-cluj-a-castigat-supercupa-romaniei-2018-id24377.html|archive-date=15 July 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nCic\u00e2ld\u0103u netted his first goal in a 3\u20130 away league win over [[FC Astra Giurgiu|Astra Giurgiu]], on 26 October.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/astra-giurgiu-cs-u-craiova-0-3-foto-video-craiova-a-facut-spectacol-la-giurgiu-si-a-urcat-pe-locul-2-mitrita-si-koljic-au-fost-de-neoprit-551658.html|title=ASTRA GIURGIU - CS U CRAIOVA 0-3 // FOTO+VIDEO Craiova a f\u0103cut spectacol la Giurgiu \u0219i a urcat pe locul 2 \u00bb Mitri\u021b\u0103 \u0219i Koljic au fost de neoprit!|trans-title=ASTRA GIURGIU - CS U CRAIOVA 0-3 // PHOTO+VIDEO Craiova impressed at Giurgiu and went up to place 2 \u00bb Mitri\u021b\u0103 \u0219i Kolji\u0107 were unstoppable!|newspaper=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian|date=26 October 2018|accessdate=2 November 2018}}</ref> He found the net again after four days, this time in the [[Cupa Rom\u00e2niei]] in an eventual 4\u20131 victory against [[AFC Turris-Oltul Turnu M\u0103gurele|Turris Turnu M\u0103gurele]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ziare.com/cupa-romaniei/rezultate/craiova-a-facut-spectacol-cu-echipa-lui-dragnea-in-cupa-romaniei-1536127|title=Craiova a facut spectacol cu echipa lui Dragnea, in Cupa Romaniei|trans-title=Craiova impressed against Dragnea's team, in the Romanian Cup|newspaper=Ziare.ro|language=Romanian|date=30 October 2018|accessdate=2 November 2018}}</ref> On 31 March 2019, Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u scored a header in a 2\u20133 away loss to [[FCSB]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digisport.ro/fotbal/liga-1/fcsb-craiova-live-video-inclestare-cu-iz-de-razboi-si-cu-miza-directa-in-lupta-pentru-titlu-echipele-probabile-636131|title=FCSB - Craiova 3-2. Rezerva Gnohere a adus victoria ro\u0219-alba\u0219trilor, dup\u0103 un meci nebun, cu gre\u0219eli mari de arbitraj|trans-title=FCSB - Craiova 3\u20132. Substitute Gnoh\u00e9r\u00e9 brought the victory of \"the Red-Blues\", after a crazy match, with many referee mistakes|newspaper=DigiSport|language=Romanian|date=31 March 2019|accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref> He recorded his first goal in [[UEFA|European competitions]] on 18 July that year, scoring the opener in a 3\u20132 home success against Azerbaijani club [[Sabail FK|Sabail]] in the second leg of the [[2019\u201320 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round|UEFA Europa League first qualifying round]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2020/matches/round=2001146/match=2027622/index.html|title=Universitatea Craiova 3\u20132 Sabail|publisher=UEFA.com|date=18 July 2019|accessdate=19 July 2019}}</ref> \n\nCic\u00e2ld\u0103u netted his first goal in a 3\u20130 away league win over [[FC Astra Giurgiu|Astra Giurgiu]], on 26 October.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/astra-giurgiu-cs-u-craiova-0-3-foto-video-craiova-a-facut-spectacol-la-giurgiu-si-a-urcat-pe-locul-2-mitrita-si-koljic-au-fost-de-neoprit-551658.html|title=ASTRA GIURGIU - CS U CRAIOVA 0-3 // FOTO+VIDEO Craiova a f\u0103cut spectacol la Giurgiu \u0219i a urcat pe locul 2 \u00bb Mitri\u021b\u0103 \u0219i Koljic au fost de neoprit!|trans-title=ASTRA GIURGIU - CS U CRAIOVA 0-3 // PHOTO+VIDEO Craiova impressed at Giurgiu and went up to place 2 \u00bb Mitri\u021b\u0103 \u0219i Kolji\u0107 were unstoppable!|newspaper=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian|date=26 October 2018|accessdate=2 November 2018}}</ref> He found the net again after four days, this time in the [[Cupa Rom\u00e2niei]] in an eventual 4\u20131 victory against [[AFC Turris-Oltul Turnu M\u0103gurele|Turris Turnu M\u0103gurele]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ziare.com/cupa-romaniei/rezultate/craiova-a-facut-spectacol-cu-echipa-lui-dragnea-in-cupa-romaniei-1536127|title=Craiova a facut spectacol cu echipa lui Dragnea, in Cupa Romaniei|trans-title=Craiova impressed against Dragnea's team, in the Romanian Cup|newspaper=Ziare.ro|language=Romanian|date=30 October 2018|accessdate=2 November 2018}}</ref> On 31 March 2019, Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u scored a header in a 2\u20133 away loss to [[FCSB]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digisport.ro/fotbal/liga-1/fcsb-craiova-live-video-inclestare-cu-iz-de-razboi-si-cu-miza-directa-in-lupta-pentru-titlu-echipele-probabile-636131|title=FCSB - Craiova 3-2. Rezerva Gnohere a adus victoria ro\u0219-alba\u0219trilor, dup\u0103 un meci nebun, cu gre\u0219eli mari de arbitraj|trans-title=FCSB - Craiova 3\u20132. Substitute Gnoh\u00e9r\u00e9 brought the victory of \"the Red-Blues\", after a crazy match, with many referee mistakes|newspaper=DigiSport|language=Romanian|date=31 March 2019|accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref> He recorded his first goal in [[UEFA|European competitions]] on 18 July that year, scoring the opener in a 3\u20132 home success against Azerbaijani club [[Sabail FK|Sabail]] in the second leg of the [[2019\u201320 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round|UEFA Europa League first qualifying round]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2020/matches/round=2001146/match=2027622/index.html|title=Universitatea Craiova 3\u20132 Sabail|publisher=UEFA.com|date=18 July 2019|accessdate=19 July 2019}}</ref> \n\nAfter prolonged speculation regarding offers from foreign teams,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digisport.ro/fotbal/liga-1/universitatea-craiova-are-oferta-de-5-milioane-de-euro-pe-masa-pentru-alexandru-cicaldau-unde-poate-ajunge-693029|title=Universitatea Craiova are ofert\u0103 de 5 milioane de euro pe mas\u0103, pentru Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u. Unde poate ajunge|trans-title=Universitatea Craiova has a 5 million euros offer on the table for Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u. Where he could turn up to|publisher=Digi Sport|language=Romanian|date=18 July 2019}}</ref> in September 2019 he signed a new contract with Craiova which would run until 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.libertatea.ro/sport/cicaldau-si-a-prelungit-contractul-cu-universitatea-craiova-pana-in-2025-2747697|title=Cicald\u0103u \u0219i-a prelungit contractul cu Universitatea Craiova p\u00e2n\u0103 \u00een 2025|trans-title=Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u extended his contract with Universitatea Craiova until 2025|newspaper=[[Libertatea]]|language=Romanian|date=15 September 2019}}</ref> On 31 January 2020, in the opening fixture of the calendar year, Cic\u00e2ldau scored twice before half-time in an eventual 3\u20131 defeat of [[CS Gaz Metan Media\u0219|Gaz Metan Media\u0219]]. The second goal came from a [[Free kick (association football)|direct free kick]], and the double\u2014which was the first in his professional career\u2014took his tally in the competition to eight goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fanatik.ro/alexandru-cicaldau-dupa-prima-dubla-din-cariera-exersez-mult-la-antrenamente-19147111|title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u, dup\u0103 prima \u201ddubl\u0103\u201d din carier\u0103: \u201dExersez mult la antrenamente\u201d|trans-title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u, after the first \"double\" of his career: \"I practice it a lot in trainings\"|publisher=Fanatik.ro|language=Romanian|date=31 January 2020|accessdate=6 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nCic\u00e2ld\u0103u received his first call up for the [[Romania national football team|Romania]] senior team in March 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://frf.ro/masculin/echipa-nationala/27-de-jucatori-convocati-pentru-dubla-cu-israel-si-suedia-id23737.html|title=27 de juc\u0103tori convoca\u021bi pentru \u201ddubla\u201d cu Israel \u0219i Suedia|trans-title=27 players called-up for the \"double\" with Israel and Sweden|publisher=[[Romanian Football Federation]]|language=Romanian|date=16 March 2018|accessdate=17 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180317102224/http://frf.ro/masculin/echipa-nationala/27-de-jucatori-convocati-pentru-dubla-cu-israel-si-suedia-id23737.html|archive-date=17 March 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the 24th that month, he made his debut as an 83rd-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] with [[Israel national football team|Israel]], which his team won 2\u20131.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digisport.ro/fotbal/echipa-nationala/israel-romania-sambata-2000-primul-meci-al-tricolorilor-din-2018-413560|title=Israel - Rom\u00e2nia 1-2. Tricolorii au revenit spectaculos \u0219i c\u00e2\u0219tig\u0103 primul amical al anului|trans-title=Israel - Romania 1\u20132. \"The Tricolours\" win the first friendly of the year|publisher=Digi Sport|language=Romanian|date=24 March 2018|accessdate=24 March 2018}}</ref> His first official game for the country came on 17 November, in a 3\u20130 [[UEFA Nations League]] defeat of [[Lithuania national football team|Lithuania]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digisport.ro/fotbal/liga-natiunilor/live-romania-lituania-ora-2145-ultimul-meci-acasa-in-liga-natiunilor-559028|title=Rom\u00e2nia - Lituania 3-0. \"Tricolorii\" au urcat pe locul 2, dup\u0103 cea mai bun\u0103 presta\u0163ie din Liga Na\u0163iunilor|trans-title=Romania - Lithuania 3\u20130. \"The Tricolours\" climbed to the second place, after their best performance in the Nations League|publisher=Digi Sport|language=Romanian|date=17 November 2018|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe following year he represented his country [[Romania national under-21 football team|under-21 side]] at the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2019 UEFA European Championship]], where they managed to progress past the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification#Group C|group stage]] before being eliminated by defending champions [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany]] in the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification#Semi-finals|semi-finals]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/season=2019/matches/round=2000800/match=2027440/index.html|title=Germany 4\u20132 Romania|publisher=UEFA.com|date=27 June 2019|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref> He earned four [[Cap (sports)|caps]] during the final tournament, all as a starter.\n\n==Style of play==\nCic\u00e2ld\u0103u is capable of aiding his teammates in both [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defense]] and [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attack]], being described as a [[Midfielder#Box-to-box midfielder|box-to-box midfielder]] by former Romanian international [[Gheorghe Craioveanu]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digisport.ro/fotbal/liga-1/va-fi-vandut-pe-8-10-milioane-de-euro-craioveanu-anunta-care-va-fi-transferul-bomba-in-liga-1-516290|title=\"Va fi v\u00e2ndut pe 8-10 milioane de euro\". Craioveanu anun\u0163\u0103 care va fi transferul bomb\u0103, \u00een Liga 1|trans-title=\"He will be sold for 8-10 million euros\". Craioveanu announces the next big transfer of Liga 1|publisher=Digi Sport|language=Romanian|date=8 September 2018|accessdate=9 September 2018}}</ref> A player with good technique, he has been noted for his [[work ethic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prosport.ro/highlight/sanmartean-lasat-masca-de-cicaldau-e-senzational-super-jucator-16777557|title=S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean, l\u0103sat masc\u0103 de Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u! \"E senza\u0163ional, super juc\u0103tor\"|trans-title=S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean, fascinated by Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u! \"He's sensational, extraordinary player\"|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian|date=22 October 2017|accessdate=6 July 2018|quote=He has a great capacity for effort, I think it was the best match he did.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fanatik.ro/alexandru-cicaldau-este-dorit-in-serie-a-de-un-club-cu-antrenor-care-a-jucat-in-romania-18991549|title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ldau, dorit de o echip\u0103 din Serie A! Anun\u0163ul de ULTIM\u0102 OR\u0102 al italienilor|trans-title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ldau, wanted by a Serie A team! The latest announcement of Italian press|publisher=Fanatik.ro|language=Romanian|date=24 June 2019|accessdate=30 June 2019|quote=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u, the offensive midfielder of Romania's U21 national team, is a technically gifted player who also manages to cover a big portion of the field, having a good effort capacity.}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 22 December 2019}}<ref>{{Soccerway|alexandru-cicaldau/319638|accessdate=24 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|National Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[League Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA#Club|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other<ref group=\"lower-alpha\">Includes the [[Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei]]</ref>\n! colspan=\"3\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[FC Viitorul Constan\u021ba|Viitorul Constan\u021ba]]\n|[[2015\u201316 Liga I|2015\u201316]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Liga I]]\n|2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||2||0\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Liga I|2016\u201317]]\n|6||0||3||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||9||0\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Liga I|2017\u201318]]\n|34||1||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||3||0||1||0||38||1\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!42!!1!!3!!0!!0!!0!!3!!0!!1!!0!!49!!1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[CS Universitatea Craiova|Universitatea Craiova]]\n|[[2018\u201319 Liga I|2018\u201319]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Liga I]]\n|35||4||5||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||2||0||1||0||43||5\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 Liga I|2019\u201320]]\n|25||10||2||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||5||1||0||0||32||12\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!60!!14!!7!!1!!\u2014!!\u2014!!7!!1!!1!!0!!75!!17\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!102!!15!!10!!2!!0!!0!!10!!1!!2!!0!!124!!18\n|}\n\n{{Reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n===International===\n{{updated|18 November 2019}}<ref name=EU>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=30218|title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u|publisher=European Football|accessdate=24 March 2018}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Romania national football team|Romania]]\n|-\n|2018||3||0\n|-\n|2019||3||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total||6||0\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n'''Viitorul Constan\u021ba'''\n*[[Liga I]]: [[2016\u201317 Liga I|2016\u201317]]\n*[[Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei]]: Runner-up [[2017 Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei|2017]]\n\n'''Universitatea Craiova'''\n*[[Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei]]: Runner-up [[2018 Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei|2018]]\n\n===Individual===\n*[[Liga I]] Team of the Season: [[2018\u201319 Liga I|2018\u201319]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{RomanianSoccer|4389/alexandru-cicaldau}}\n*{{NFT player|70854}}\n*{{UEFA player|250066711}}\n\n{{CS Universitatea Craiova squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cicaldau, Alexandru}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Medgidia]]\n[[Category:Romanian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Liga I players]]\n[[Category:FC Viitorul Constan\u021ba players]]\n[[Category:CS Universitatea Craiova players]]\n[[Category:Romania youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Romania under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Romania international footballers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u\n| image = \n| fullname = Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1997|07|08|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Medgidia]], Romania\n| height = 1.78m\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[CS Universitatea Craiova|Universitatea Craiova]]\n| clubnumber = 10\n| youthyears1 = 2010\u20132015\n| youthclubs1 = [[Gheorghe Hagi Football Academy|Gheorghe Hagi Academy]]\n| years1 = 2016\u20132018\n| clubs1 = [[FC Viitorul Constan\u021ba|Viitorul Constan\u021ba]]\n| caps1 = 42\n| goals1 = 1\n| years2 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs2 = [[CS Universitatea Craiova|Universitatea Craiova]]\n| caps2 = 60\n| goals2 = 14\n| nationalyears1 = 2015\u20132016\n| nationalteam1 = [[Romania national under-19 football team|Romania U19]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 6\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2017\u20132019\n| nationalteam2 = [[Romania national under-21 football team|Romania U21]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 13\n| nationalgoals2 = 2\n| nationalyears3 = 2018\u2013\n| nationalteam3 = [[Romania national football team|Romania]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 6\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| pcupdate = {{date|2020-01-31}}\n| ntupdate = {{date|2019-11-18}}\n}}\n\n'''Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u''' ({{IPA-ro|alek\u02c8sandru t\u0283ik\u0268l\u02c8d\u0259w}}; born 8 July 1997) is a Romanian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[CS Universitatea Craiova]] and the [[Romania national football team|Romania national team]].\n\nHe started his career at [[FC Viitorul Constan\u021ba|Viitorul Constan\u021ba]], recording his professional debut with the team in 2016. Two years later, he transferred to Universitatea Craiova.\n\nCic\u00e2ld\u0103u made his full international debut for [[Romania national football team|Romania]] in March 2018.\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Early years / Viitorul Constan\u021ba===\nCic\u00e2ld\u0103u was raised in [[Mircea Vod\u0103, Constan\u021ba|Satu Nou]], a village near [[Medgidia]], [[Constan\u021ba County]], and started playing football at the age of 8. He later joined the [[Gheorghe Hagi Football Academy|Gheorghe Hagi Academy]], which serves as the youth setup of [[FC Viitorul Constan\u021ba|Viitorul Constan\u021ba]].<ref name=\"GSP_interview\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/foto-exclusiv-cicaldau-a-parasit-cantonamentul-viitorului-si-vine-la-bucuresti-sa-semneze-cu-noua-echipa-543406.html|title=Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u a p\u0103r\u0103sit cantonamentul Viitorului \u0219i vine la Bucure\u0219ti s\u0103 semneze cu noua echip\u0103!|trans-title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u left Viitorul and is travelling to Bucharest to sign for a new team|newspaper=[[Gazeta Sporturilor]]|language=Romanian|date=5 July 2018|accessdate=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nCic\u00e2ld\u0103u made his debut in the [[Liga I|first division]] for Viitorul on 31 March 2016, aged 18, in a 1\u20131 away draw with [[ASA 2013 T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219|ASA T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digisport.ro/live-text/asa-tg-mures-viitorul-1-1-gazdele-au-salvat-un-punct-pe-final-eroare-uriasa-pecanha-300495|title=ASA Tg. Mure\u0219 - Viitorul 1-1|publisher=[[Digi Sport (Romania)|Digi Sport]]|language=Romanian|date=31 March 2016|accessdate=25 March 2018}}</ref> He became a regular starter for the club in the [[2017\u201318 Liga I|2017\u201318 season]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prosport.ro/video/fotbal-intern/nationala/interviu-video-da-la-inceput-eram-doar-un-pusti-promitator-ca-la-20-de-ani-fara-griji-dar-adulat-de-fani-cicaldau-vorbeste-despre-hagi-interesul-lui-becali-si-nationala-de-tineret-16814461|title=INTERVIU VIDEO &#124; \"Da! La \u00eenceput eram doar un pu\u015fti promi\u0163\u0103tor\". Ca la 20 de ani, f\u0103r\u0103 griji dar adulat de fani. Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u vorbe\u015fte despre Hagi, interesul lui Becali \u015fi na\u0163ionala de tineret|trans-title=VIDEO INTERVIEW &#124; \"Yes! At first I was just a promising youth.\" Like a 20-year-old, without worries but beloved by fans. Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u talks about Hagi, Becali's interest and the youth national team|publisher=[[ProSport]]|language=Romanian|date=10 November 2017|accessdate=25 March 2018}}</ref> amassing 38 appearances and one goal in all competitions.\n\n===Universitatea Craiova===\nOn 6 July 2018, Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u agreed to a four-year contract with [[CS Universitatea Craiova]], being assigned the [[Squad number (association football)|number 10 shirt]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ucv1948.ro/Alexandru-Cicaldau-jucatorul-Stiintei-pentru-4-ani|title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u, juc\u0103torul \u0218tiin\u021bei pentru 4 ani!|trans-title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u, the player of ''\u0218tiin\u021ba'' for the next 4 years!|publisher=CS Universitatea Craiova|language=Romanian|date=6 July 2018|accessdate=6 July 2018}}</ref> Press reported the fee at figures between [[Euro|\u20ac]]750,000 and \u20ac1 million plus interest on the capital gain of a potential future transfer.<ref name=\"GSP_interview\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sport.ro/liga-1/transfer-urias-in-liga-1-unul-dintre-cei-mai-doriti-jucatori-a-ales-o-pe-craiova-dupa-ce-a-refuzat-fcsb.html|title=Transfer URIAS in Liga 1! Unul dintre cei mai doriti jucatori a ales-o pe Craiova dupa ce a refuzat FCSB si CFR Cluj! Anuntul diminetii|trans-title=HUGE transfer in Liga 1! One of the most desired players chose Craiova after rejecting FCSB and CFR Cluj!|publisher=[[Sport.ro]]|language=Romanian|date=5 July 2018|accessdate=6 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/cati-bani-primeste-hagi-pentru-transferul-lui-cicaldau-suma-care-l-a-convins-pe-rege-sa-si-vanda-unul-dintre-cei-mai-buni-fotbalisti-la-craiova-17345369|title=C\u00e2\u0163i bani prime\u015fte Hagi pentru transferul lui Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u. Suma care l-a convins pe \"Rege\" s\u0103-\u015fi v\u00e2nd\u0103 unul dintre cei mai buni fotbali\u015fti la Craiova|trans-title=How much money Hagi receives for the transfer of Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u. The sum that convinced \"the King\" to sell one of his best footballers to Craiova|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian|date=6 July 2018|accessdate=6 July 2018}}</ref> He made his first appearance for \"the White-Blues\" eight days later in the [[2018 Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei|Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei]], playing the full match as [[CFR Cluj]] came victorious 1\u20130.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://frf.ro/competitii/competitii-masculin/cfr-cluj-a-castigat-supercupa-romaniei-2018-id24377.html|title=CFR Cluj a c\u00e2\u0219tigat Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei 2018|trans-title=CFR Cluj won the 2018 Romanian Supercup|publisher=[[Romanian Football Federation]]|language=Romanian|date=14 July 2018|accessdate=15 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180715011429/http://frf.ro/competitii/competitii-masculin/cfr-cluj-a-castigat-supercupa-romaniei-2018-id24377.html|archive-date=15 July 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nCic\u00e2ld\u0103u netted his first goal in a 3\u20130 away league win over [[FC Astra Giurgiu|Astra Giurgiu]], on 26 October.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/astra-giurgiu-cs-u-craiova-0-3-foto-video-craiova-a-facut-spectacol-la-giurgiu-si-a-urcat-pe-locul-2-mitrita-si-koljic-au-fost-de-neoprit-551658.html|title=ASTRA GIURGIU - CS U CRAIOVA 0-3 // FOTO+VIDEO Craiova a f\u0103cut spectacol la Giurgiu \u0219i a urcat pe locul 2 \u00bb Mitri\u021b\u0103 \u0219i Koljic au fost de neoprit!|trans-title=ASTRA GIURGIU - CS U CRAIOVA 0-3 // PHOTO+VIDEO Craiova impressed at Giurgiu and went up to place 2 \u00bb Mitri\u021b\u0103 \u0219i Kolji\u0107 were unstoppable!|newspaper=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian|date=26 October 2018|accessdate=2 November 2018}}</ref> He found the net again after four days, this time in the [[Cupa Rom\u00e2niei]] in an eventual 4\u20131 victory against [[AFC Turris-Oltul Turnu M\u0103gurele|Turris Turnu M\u0103gurele]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ziare.com/cupa-romaniei/rezultate/craiova-a-facut-spectacol-cu-echipa-lui-dragnea-in-cupa-romaniei-1536127|title=Craiova a facut spectacol cu echipa lui Dragnea, in Cupa Romaniei|trans-title=Craiova impressed against Dragnea's team, in the Romanian Cup|newspaper=Ziare.ro|language=Romanian|date=30 October 2018|accessdate=2 November 2018}}</ref> On 31 March 2019, Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u scored a header in a 2\u20133 away loss to [[FCSB]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digisport.ro/fotbal/liga-1/fcsb-craiova-live-video-inclestare-cu-iz-de-razboi-si-cu-miza-directa-in-lupta-pentru-titlu-echipele-probabile-636131|title=FCSB - Craiova 3-2. Rezerva Gnohere a adus victoria ro\u0219-alba\u0219trilor, dup\u0103 un meci nebun, cu gre\u0219eli mari de arbitraj|trans-title=FCSB - Craiova 3\u20132. Substitute Gnoh\u00e9r\u00e9 brought the victory of \"the Red-Blues\", after a crazy match, with many referee mistakes|newspaper=DigiSport|language=Romanian|date=31 March 2019|accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref> He recorded his first goal in [[UEFA|European competitions]] on 18 July that year, scoring the opener in a 3\u20132 home success against Azerbaijani club [[Sabail FK|Sabail]] in the second leg of the [[2019\u201320 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round|UEFA Europa League first qualifying round]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2020/matches/round=2001146/match=2027622/index.html|title=Universitatea Craiova 3\u20132 Sabail|publisher=UEFA.com|date=18 July 2019|accessdate=19 July 2019}}</ref> \n\nic\u00e2ld\u0103u netted his first goal in a 3\u20130 away league win over [[FC Astra Giurgiu|Astra Giurgiu]], on 26 October.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/astra-giurgiu-cs-u-craiova-0-3-foto-video-craiova-a-facut-spectacol-la-giurgiu-si-a-urcat-pe-locul-2-mitrita-si-koljic-au-fost-de-neoprit-551658.html|title=ASTRA GIURGIU - CS U CRAIOVA 0-3 // FOTO+VIDEO Craiova a f\u0103cut spectacol la Giurgiu \u0219i a urcat pe locul 2 \u00bb Mitri\u021b\u0103 \u0219i Koljic au fost de neoprit!|trans-title=ASTRA GIURGIU - CS U CRAIOVA 0-3 // PHOTO+VIDEO Craiova impressed at Giurgiu and went up to place 2 \u00bb Mitri\u021b\u0103 \u0219i Kolji\u0107 were unstoppable!|newspaper=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian|date=26 October 2018|accessdate=2 November 2018}}</ref> He found the net again after four days, this time in the [[Cupa Rom\u00e2niei]] in an eventual 4\u20131 victory against [[AFC Turris-Oltul Turnu M\u0103gurele|Turris Turnu M\u0103gurele]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ziare.com/cupa-romaniei/rezultate/craiova-a-facut-spectacol-cu-echipa-lui-dragnea-in-cupa-romaniei-1536127|title=Craiova a facut spectacol cu echipa lui Dragnea, in Cupa Romaniei|trans-title=Craiova impressed against Dragnea's team, in the Romanian Cup|newspaper=Ziare.ro|language=Romanian|date=30 October 2018|accessdate=2 November 2018}}</ref> On 31 March 2019, Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u scored a header in a 2\u20133 away loss to [[FCSB]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digisport.ro/fotbal/liga-1/fcsb-craiova-live-video-inclestare-cu-iz-de-razboi-si-cu-miza-directa-in-lupta-pentru-titlu-echipele-probabile-636131|title=FCSB - Craiova 3-2. Rezerva Gnohere a adus victoria ro\u0219-alba\u0219trilor, dup\u0103 un meci nebun, cu gre\u0219eli mari de arbitraj|trans-title=FCSB - Craiova 3\u20132. Substitute Gnoh\u00e9r\u00e9 brought the victory of \"the Red-Blues\", after a crazy match, with many referee mistakes|newspaper=DigiSport|language=Romanian|date=31 March 2019|accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref> He recorded his first goal in [[UEFA|European competitions]] on 18 July that year, scoring the opener in a 3\u20132 home success against Azerbaijani club [[Sabail FK|Sabail]] in the second leg of the [[2019\u201320 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round|UEFA Europa League first qualifying round]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2020/matches/round=2001146/match=2027622/index.html|title=Universitatea Craiova 3\u20132 Sabail|publisher=UEFA.com|date=18 July 2019|accessdate=19 July 2019}}</ref> \n\nAfter prolonged speculation regarding offers from foreign teams,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digisport.ro/fotbal/liga-1/universitatea-craiova-are-oferta-de-5-milioane-de-euro-pe-masa-pentru-alexandru-cicaldau-unde-poate-ajunge-693029|title=Universitatea Craiova are ofert\u0103 de 5 milioane de euro pe mas\u0103, pentru Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u. Unde poate ajunge|trans-title=Universitatea Craiova has a 5 million euros offer on the table for Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u. Where he could turn up to|publisher=Digi Sport|language=Romanian|date=18 July 2019}}</ref> in September 2019 he signed a new contract with Craiova which would run until 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.libertatea.ro/sport/cicaldau-si-a-prelungit-contractul-cu-universitatea-craiova-pana-in-2025-2747697|title=Cicald\u0103u \u0219i-a prelungit contractul cu Universitatea Craiova p\u00e2n\u0103 \u00een 2025|trans-title=Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u extended his contract with Universitatea Craiova until 2025|newspaper=[[Libertatea]]|language=Romanian|date=15 September 2019}}</ref> On 31 January 2020, in the opening fixture of the calendar year, Cic\u00e2ldau scored twice before half-time in an eventual 3\u20131 defeat of [[CS Gaz Metan Media\u0219|Gaz Metan Media\u0219]]. The second goal came from a [[Free kick (association football)|direct free kick]], and the double\u2014which was the first in his professional career\u2014took his tally in the competition to eight goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fanatik.ro/alexandru-cicaldau-dupa-prima-dubla-din-cariera-exersez-mult-la-antrenamente-19147111|title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u, dup\u0103 prima \u201ddubl\u0103\u201d din carier\u0103: \u201dExersez mult la antrenamente\u201d|trans-title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u, after the first \"double\" of his career: \"I practice it a lot in trainings\"|publisher=Fanatik.ro|language=Romanian|date=31 January 2020|accessdate=6 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nCic\u00e2ld\u0103u received his first call up for the [[Romania national football team|Romania]] senior team in March 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://frf.ro/masculin/echipa-nationala/27-de-jucatori-convocati-pentru-dubla-cu-israel-si-suedia-id23737.html|title=27 de juc\u0103tori convoca\u021bi pentru \u201ddubla\u201d cu Israel \u0219i Suedia|trans-title=27 players called-up for the \"double\" with Israel and Sweden|publisher=[[Romanian Football Federation]]|language=Romanian|date=16 March 2018|accessdate=17 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180317102224/http://frf.ro/masculin/echipa-nationala/27-de-jucatori-convocati-pentru-dubla-cu-israel-si-suedia-id23737.html|archive-date=17 March 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the 24th that month, he made his debut as an 83rd-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] with [[Israel national football team|Israel]], which his team won 2\u20131.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digisport.ro/fotbal/echipa-nationala/israel-romania-sambata-2000-primul-meci-al-tricolorilor-din-2018-413560|title=Israel - Rom\u00e2nia 1-2. Tricolorii au revenit spectaculos \u0219i c\u00e2\u0219tig\u0103 primul amical al anului|trans-title=Israel - Romania 1\u20132. \"The Tricolours\" win the first friendly of the year|publisher=Digi Sport|language=Romanian|date=24 March 2018|accessdate=24 March 2018}}</ref> His first official game for the country came on 17 November, in a 3\u20130 [[UEFA Nations League]] defeat of [[Lithuania national football team|Lithuania]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digisport.ro/fotbal/liga-natiunilor/live-romania-lituania-ora-2145-ultimul-meci-acasa-in-liga-natiunilor-559028|title=Rom\u00e2nia - Lituania 3-0. \"Tricolorii\" au urcat pe locul 2, dup\u0103 cea mai bun\u0103 presta\u0163ie din Liga Na\u0163iunilor|trans-title=Romania - Lithuania 3\u20130. \"The Tricolours\" climbed to the second place, after their best performance in the Nations League|publisher=Digi Sport|language=Romanian|date=17 November 2018|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe following year he represented his country [[Romania national under-21 football team|under-21 side]] at the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2019 UEFA European Championship]], where they managed to progress past the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification#Group C|group stage]] before being eliminated by defending champions [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany]] in the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification#Semi-finals|semi-finals]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/season=2019/matches/round=2000800/match=2027440/index.html|title=Germany 4\u20132 Romania|publisher=UEFA.com|date=27 June 2019|accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref> He earned four [[Cap (sports)|caps]] during the final tournament, all as a starter.\n\n==Style of play==\nCic\u00e2ld\u0103u is capable of aiding his teammates in both [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defense]] and [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attack]], being described as a [[Midfielder#Box-to-box midfielder|box-to-box midfielder]] by former Romanian international [[Gheorghe Craioveanu]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digisport.ro/fotbal/liga-1/va-fi-vandut-pe-8-10-milioane-de-euro-craioveanu-anunta-care-va-fi-transferul-bomba-in-liga-1-516290|title=\"Va fi v\u00e2ndut pe 8-10 milioane de euro\". Craioveanu anun\u0163\u0103 care va fi transferul bomb\u0103, \u00een Liga 1|trans-title=\"He will be sold for 8-10 million euros\". Craioveanu announces the next big transfer of Liga 1|publisher=Digi Sport|language=Romanian|date=8 September 2018|accessdate=9 September 2018}}</ref> A player with good technique, he has been noted for his [[work ethic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prosport.ro/highlight/sanmartean-lasat-masca-de-cicaldau-e-senzational-super-jucator-16777557|title=S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean, l\u0103sat masc\u0103 de Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u! \"E senza\u0163ional, super juc\u0103tor\"|trans-title=S\u00e2nm\u0103rtean, fascinated by Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u! \"He's sensational, extraordinary player\"|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian|date=22 October 2017|accessdate=6 July 2018|quote=He has a great capacity for effort, I think it was the best match he did.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fanatik.ro/alexandru-cicaldau-este-dorit-in-serie-a-de-un-club-cu-antrenor-care-a-jucat-in-romania-18991549|title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ldau, dorit de o echip\u0103 din Serie A! Anun\u0163ul de ULTIM\u0102 OR\u0102 al italienilor|trans-title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ldau, wanted by a Serie A team! The latest announcement of Italian press|publisher=Fanatik.ro|language=Romanian|date=24 June 2019|accessdate=30 June 2019|quote=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u, the offensive midfielder of Romania's U21 national team, is a technically gifted player who also manages to cover a big portion of the field, having a good effort capacity.}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 22 December 2019}}<ref>{{Soccerway|alexandru-cicaldau/319638|accessdate=24 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|National Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[League Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA#Club|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other<ref group=\"lower-alpha\">Includes the [[Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei]]</ref>\n! colspan=\"3\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[FC Viitorul Constan\u021ba|Viitorul Constan\u021ba]]\n|[[2015\u201316 Liga I|2015\u201316]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Liga I]]\n|2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||2||0\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Liga I|2016\u201317]]\n|6||0||3||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||9||0\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Liga I|2017\u201318]]\n|34||1||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||3||0||1||0||38||1\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!42!!1!!3!!0!!0!!0!!3!!0!!1!!0!!49!!1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[CS Universitatea Craiova|Universitatea Craiova]]\n|[[2018\u201319 Liga I|2018\u201319]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Liga I]]\n|35||4||5||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||2||0||1||0||43||5\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 Liga I|2019\u201320]]\n|25||10||2||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||5||1||0||0||32||12\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!60!!14!!7!!1!!\u2014!!\u2014!!7!!1!!1!!0!!75!!17\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!102!!15!!10!!2!!0!!0!!10!!1!!2!!0!!124!!18\n|}\n\n{{Reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n===International===\n{{updated|18 November 2019}}<ref name=EU>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=30218|title=Alexandru Cic\u00e2ld\u0103u|publisher=European Football|accessdate=24 March 2018}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Romania national football team|Romania]]\n|-\n|2018||3||0\n|-\n|2019||3||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total||6||0\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n'''Viitorul Constan\u021ba'''\n*[[Liga I]]: [[2016\u201317 Liga I|2016\u201317]]\n*[[Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei]]: Runner-up [[2017 Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei|2017]]\n\n'''Universitatea Craiova'''\n*[[Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei]]: Runner-up [[2018 Supercupa Rom\u00e2niei|2018]]\n\n===Individual===\n*[[Liga I]] Team of the Season: [[2018\u201319 Liga I|2018\u201319]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{RomanianSoccer|4389/alexandru-cicaldau}}\n*{{NFT player|70854}}\n*{{UEFA player|250066711}}\n\n{{CS Universitatea Craiova squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cicaldau, Alexandru}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Medgidia]]\n[[Category:Romanian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Liga I players]]\n[[Category:FC Viitorul Constan\u021ba players]]\n[[Category:CS Universitatea Craiova players]]\n[[Category:Romania youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Romania under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Romania international footballers]]\n", "name_user": "8Dodo8", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eUniversitatea Craiova", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexandru_Cic%C3%A2ld%C4%83u"}
{"title_page": "Dellafuente", "text_new": "\n\n\n'''Pablo Enoc Bayo''', (Granada, 14 de septiembre de 1991)\n", "text_old": "#REDIRECT [[Mala Rodr\u00edguez]]\n", "name_user": "Jorgepj02", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Dellafuente&redirect=no"}
{"title_page": "T2K experiment", "text_new": "{{primary sources|date=September 2012}}\n\n'''T2K''' ('''[[T\u014dkai, Ibaraki|Tokai]] to [[Kamioka, Gifu|Kamioka]]''') is a [[particle physics]] experiment studying the [[neutrino oscillations|oscillations]] of the [[accelerator neutrinos]]. The experiment is conducted in [[Japan]] by the international cooperation of about 500 physicists and engineers with over 60 research institutions from several countries from [[Europe]], [[Asia]] and [[North America]] <ref name=\"t2knim\">{{cite web |title=The T2K experiment collaboration |url=https://t2k-experiment.org/t2k/collaboration/}}</ref> and it is a recognized [[CERN]] experiment (RE13) <ref>{{cite web |url=http://committees.web.cern.ch/rec/welcome.html|title=Recognized Experiments at CERN |website=The CERN Scientific Committees |publisher=CERN |access-date=20 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://greybook.cern.ch/greybook/experiment/detail?id=RE13 |title=RE13/T2K : The long-baseline neutrino experiment |website=The CERN Experimental Programme |publisher=CERN |access-date=20 January 2020}}</ref>.\n\nT2K was the first experiment which observed the appearance of [[electron neutrino]]s in [[muon neutrino]] [[particle beam|beam]] <ref>[http://press.cern/press-releases/2010/05/particle-chameleon-caught-act-changing Particle Chameleon Caught in the act of Changing], CERN press release</ref><ref name=\"1106.2822\">{{Cite journal|arxiv=1106.2822 |author1=T2K Collaboration |title=Indication of Electron Neutrino Appearance from an Accelerator-produced Off-axis Muon Neutrino Beam |journal=Physical Review Letters |volume=107 |issue=4 |pages=041801 |year=2011 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.107.041801 |pmid=21866992 |bibcode = 2011PhRvL.107d1801A }}</ref>, it also provided the world best measurement of oscillation parameter ''\u03b8''<sub>23</sub> <ref name=\"1403.1532\">{{Cite journal|arxiv=1403.1532 |author1=T2K Collaboration | title=Precise Measurement of the Neutrino Mixing Parameter \\theta_{23} from Muon Neutrino Disappearance in an Off-Axis Beam | journal=Phys. Rev. Lett. |volume=112 | pages=181801 |year=2014 | doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.112.181801 }}</ref> and a hint of a significant [[CP violation|matter-antimatter asymmetry]] in neutrino oscillations <ref>{{Cite journal|arxiv=1502.01550 |author1=T2K Collaboration | title=Measurements of neutrino oscillation in appearance and disappearance channels by the T2K experiment with 6.6\u00d710$^{20}$ protons on target | journal=Phys. Rev. |volume=D91 | pages=072010 |year=2015 | doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.91.072010 }}</ref><ref name=\"1910.03887\">{{Cite journal|arxiv=1910.03887 |author1=T2K Collaboration | title=Constraint on the Matter-Antimatter Symmetry-Violating Phase in Neutrino Oscillations |year=2019 }}</ref>. The measurement of the neutrino-antineutrino oscillation asymmetry may bring us closer to the explanation of the existence of our [[Baryon asymmetry|matter-dominated]] Universe.\n\nThe intense beam of muon neutrinos is produced in the [[J-PARC]] facility (Japan Proton Accelerator Research Complex) in Tokai on the east coast of Japan. The beam is directed towards the [[Super-Kamiokande]] far detector located  295 km away in [[Hida, Gifu|Hida]]-city [[Gifu prefecture|Gifu]]. The properties and composition of the neutrino flux are first measured by a system of near detectors located 280 m from the beam production place at the J-PARC site, and then again in the Super-Kamiokande detector. Comparison of the content of different neutrino flavours in these two locations allows measurement of the oscillations probability on the way between near and far detectors. Super-Kamiokande is able to detect interactions of both, muon and electron neutrinos, and thus measure the disappearance of muon neutrino flux, as well as electron neutrino appearance in the beam.\n\n==Physics program==\n\nT2K experiment was  proposed in 2003 with the following measurement goals <ref name=\"1106.1238\">{{Cite journal|author=T2K Collaboration |year=2011 |title=The T2K Experiment |journal=Nuclear Instruments and Methods in Physics Research Section A: Accelerators, Spectrometers, Detectors and Associated Equipment |volume=659 |pages=106 |arxiv=1106.1238 |doi=10.1016/j.nima.2011.06.067 |bibcode = 2011NIMPA.659..106T }}</ref>:\n* The discovery of the {{SubatomicParticle|Muon neutrino}} \u2192 {{SubatomicParticle|Electron neutrino}} oscillations, and thus the confirmation that the last unknown mixing angle ''\u03b8''<sub>13</sub> is not zero\n* precise measurement of the oscillation parameters \u0394''m''{{su|b=23|p=2}} and ''\u03b8''<sub>23</sub> via muon neutrino disappearance studies\n* Search for sterile neutrino oscillations, which cause be observed as a deficit of  neutral current neutrino interactions\n* Measurements of various interaction [[cross section (physics)|cross-sections]] for different types of neutrinos and targets in an energy range of few GeV\n\nSince the start of the data taking in 2010, the T2K experiment succeeded to provide a list of world-class results:\n* The confirmation of electron neutrino appearance in the muon neutrino beam ({{SubatomicParticle|Muon neutrino}}\u2192{{SubatomicParticle|Electron neutrino}}), which was the first time when neutrinos produced in one flavour was explicitly observed in another flavour. <ref name=\"1106.2822\" /><ref name=\"1304.0841\">{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=Evidence of electron neutrino appearance in a muon neutrino beam |journal=Physical Review D |date=5 August 2013 |volume=88 |issue=3 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.88.032002|arxiv=1304.0841}}</ref>\n* The most precise measurement of the ''\u03b8''<sub>23</sub> parameter. <ref name=\"1403.1532\" />\n* The first significant constraint on the ''\u03b4''<sub>CP</sub> parameter, responsible for the matter-antimatter asymmetry in the neutrino sector. <ref name=\"1910.03887\" />\n* Limits on a [[sterile neutrino]] oscillation parameters based on studies in the near ND280 <ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration | |title=Search for short baseline disappearance with the T2K near detector |journal=Physical Review D |date=16 March 2015 |volume=91 |issue=5 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.91.051102 |arxiv=1410.8811}}</ref> and far Super-Kamiokande <ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=Search for light sterile neutrinos with the T2K far detector Super-Kamiokande at a baseline of 295\u00a0km |journal=Physical Review D |date=30 April 2019 |volume=99 |issue=7 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.99.071103 |arxiv=1902.06529}}</ref> detectors.\n* Various cross-section measurements of electron<ref>{{cite journal | author=T2K Collaboration |title=Measurement of the charged-current electron (anti-)neutrino inclusive cross-sections at the T2K off-axis near detector ND280 |journal=arXiv:2002.11986 [hep-ex] |date=27 February 2020 | arxiv=2002.11986}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=Measurement of the electron neutrino charged-current interaction rate on water with the T2K ND280 pi0 detector |journal=Physical Review D |date=19 June 2015 |volume=91 |issue=11 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.91.112010}}</ref> and muon neutrino and antineutrino, including inclusive charged current (CC) interactions<ref>{{cite journal | author=T2K Collaboration |title=Measurement of the inclusive numu charged current cross section on carbon in the near detector of the T2K experiment |journal=Physical Review D |date=7 May 2013 |volume=87 |issue=9 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.87.092003|arxiv=1302.4908}}</ref>, CC interactions without pions <ref>{{cite journal | author=T2K Collaboration | |title=Measurement of double-differential muon neutrino charged-current interactions on C8H8 without pions in the final state using the T2K off-axis beam |journal=Physical Review D |date=21 June 2016 |volume=93 |issue=11 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.93.112012|arxiv=1602.03652}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration|title=Measurement of the numu charged-current quasielastic cross section on carbon with the ND280 detector at T2K |journal=Physical Review D |date=11 December 2015 |volume=92 |issue=11 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.92.112003|arxiv=1411.6264}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=First combined measurement of the muon neutrino and antineutrino charged-current cross section without pions in the final state at T2K |journal=arXiv:2002.09323 [hep-ex] |date=21 February 2020 |arxiv=2002.09323}}</ref> and with single pion in the final state<ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=First measurement of the muon neutrino charged current single pion production cross section on water with the T2K near detector |journal=Physical Review D |date=26 January 2017 |volume=95 |issue=1 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.95.012010|arxiv=1605.07964}}</ref>, coherent pion production<ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=Measurement of Coherent pi+ Production in Low Energy Neutrino-Carbon Scattering |journal=Physical Review Letters |date=4 November 2016 |volume=117 |issue=19 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.117.192501|arxiv=1604.04406}}</ref>, neutral current interactions<ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=Measurement of the neutrino-oxygen neutral-current interaction cross section by observing nuclear deexcitation gamma rays |journal=Physical Review D |date=31 October 2014 |volume=90 |issue=7 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.90.072012|arxiv=1403.3140}}</ref>, etc. on different targets such as carbon, water and iron<ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=Measurement of the muon neutrino charged-current cross sections on water, hydrocarbon and iron, and their ratios, with the T2K on-axis detectors |journal=Progress of Theoretical and Experimental Physics |date=September 2019 |volume=2019 |issue=9 |doi=10.1093/ptep/ptz070}}</ref>.\n\nFuture upgrades to T2K is expected to provide further constrain on the ''\u03b4''<sub>CP</sub> phase by comparing oscillations of neutrinos to those of antineutrinos, as well as more precise measurements of \u0394''m''{{su|b=23|p=2}} and ''\u03b8''<sub>23</sub> parameters, and cross-section measurements which will extend our understanding of neutrino interactions and thus improve theoretical models used in neutrino generators.<ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=Proposal for an Extended Run of T2K to $20\\times10^{21}$ POT |journal=arXiv:1609.04111 [hep-ex, physics:physics] |date=13 September 2016 |arxiv=1609.04111}}</ref><ref name=\"1805.04163\">{{cite journal |author=Hyper-Kamiokande Collaboration |title=Hyper-Kamiokande Design Report |journal=arXiv:1805.04163 [astro-ph, physics:hep-ex, physics:physics] |date=28 November 2018 |arxiv=1805.04163}}</ref>\n\n==Neutrino beam==\n\n[[File:The entire view of J-PARC.jpg|thumb|Bird's-eye view of the entire facility]]\n[[File:Superconducting Magnets J-PARC.jpg|thumb|Superconducting magnets under construction in 2008 to veer the proton beam to the direction of Kamioka]]\n[[File:J-PARC Neutrino Experiment Facility Primary Beamline Final Focusing Section.jpg|thumb|Final stage of the proton beam line before target to generate neutrino beam]]\nT2K uses a muon neutrino or muon antineutrino [[accelerator neutrino|beam]] produced at the [[J-PARC]] facility using a proton beam gradually accelerated to 30 GeV by a system of three [[particle accelerator|accelerators]]: first to 400 MeV energy by the Linac linear accelerator, then up to 3 GeV by the RCS (Rapid Cycle Synchrotron), and finally up to 30 GeV by the MR [[synchrotron]] (Main Ring). [[Proton]]s collide with a [[graphite]] target, producing [[meson]]s, mainly [[pion]]s and [[kaon]]s, which are then focused by a set of three [[magnetic horn]]s and directed into a tunnel called the decay volume. Depending on the horns polarity, either positive or negative particles are focused. Positive pions and kaons decay mainly into {{SubatomicParticle|Muon+}} and {{SubatomicParticle|Muon neutrino}}, forming a muon neutrino beam, while negative pions and kaons decay mainly into {{SubatomicParticle|Muon-}} and {{SubatomicParticle|Muon antineutrino}}, forming a muon antineutrino beam. All remaining [[hadron]]s and charged [[lepton]]s are stopped by a 75-ton block of graphite (so-called beam dump) and in the ground, while neutrinos travel underground towards the far detector.<ref name=\"t2knim\"/>\n\n===Off-axis beam===\n\nT2K is the first experiment in which the concept of off-axis [[accelerator neutrino|neutrino beam]] was realized. The neutrino beam at J-PARC is designed so that it can be directed 2 to 3 [[degree (angle)|degrees]] away from the [[Super-Kamiokande]] far detector and one of the near detectors, ND280. The off-axis angle was chosen to 2.5\u00b0 to maximize the probability of oscillation at a distance corresponding to the far detector, which for 295&nbsp;km is maximal for around 600&nbsp;MeV neutrinos. In this neutrino energy range, the dominant type of neutrino interactions are charged current quasielastic interactions, for which it is possible to reconstruct the energy of the interacting neutrino only on the basis of the momentum and direction of the produced charged lepton. The higher neutrino energies are suppressed by the off-axis configuration, decreasing the number of interactions with meson production, which are background in the oscillation analysis in the T2K experiment.<ref name=\"t2knim\"/><ref name=\"t2kflux\">{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=T2K neutrino flux prediction |journal=Physical Review D |date=2 January 2013 |volume=87 |issue=1 |doi=10.1103/physrevd.87.012001|arxiv=1211.0469}}</ref>\n\n==Near detectors==\n\nThe near detector complex is located at a distance of 280 meters from the graphite target. Its purpose is to measure the neutrino flux before oscillations and to study neutrino interactions. The system consists of three main detectors:\n* INGRID detector (Interactive Neutrino GRID) located on the axis of the neutrino beam,\n* ND280 detector located 2.5\u00b0 away from the beam axis, i.e. at the same angle as the far detector.\n* Wagasci-BabyMIND is a magnetised neutrino detector located at 1.5\u00b0 off-axis angle, built to explore the energy spectrum variation with the off-axis angle and cross-sections at higher average neutrino energy.\n\n===Signal readout===\n\nExcept for the Time Projection Chambres in ND280, the entire active material (enabling particle tracking) of the near detectors is plastic scintillator. The light produced by traversing particles in the plastic [[scintillator]] bars and planes is collected by wavelength-shifting fibres and detected by Hamamatsu Multi-pixel photon counters installed/located at one or both ends of the fibres. Scintillator bars are organised into layers, where bars in two neighbouring layers are perpendicular to each other providing together 3D information about traversing particles.\n\n===INGRID detector===\n\nThe main purpose of the INGRID detector is the monitoring of the direction and intensity of the beam on a daily basis by direct detection of neutrino interactions. The INGRID detector consists of 16 identical modules arranged in the shape of a cross, 7 in a vertical and 7 in a horizontal arm, plus 2 modules outside the cross. Height and width of the arms are 10 meters. A single module consists of alternating layers of iron and a plastic scintillator. An additional 4 veto layers of the scintillator surround the module on the sides to distinguish particles entering from the outside from those produced by interactions inside the module. The total mass of iron in one module is 7.1 tons and constitutes 96% of the module weight. On the neutrino beam axis, in the middle of the cross between the vertical and horizontal arm, there is an additional module built only from layers of the plastic scintillator (Proton Module) with a mass of 0.55 tons. Its purpose is to register quasielastic interactions and compare the obtained results with the simulations.\n\n===ND280 detector===\n\n[[File:J-PARC T2K ND280 Pit.jpg|thumb|ND280 under construction]]\nThe ND280 detector is used to measure the flux, energy spectrum and electron neutrino beam pollution for the same off-axis angle as for the far detector. ND280 also investigates various types of muon and electron neutrino and antineutrino interactions. All this allows estimating the expected number and type of interactions in the far detector, reducing the systematic error in the neutrino oscillations analysis associated with models of neutrino interactions and flux.\n\nND280 is composed of the set of inner sub-detectors: Pi-Zero detector and a tracker with 2 Fine-Grained Detectors interleaved with 3 Time Projection Chambres, placed inside of a metal frame called a basket. The basket is surrounded by the electromagnetic calorimeter and a magnet recycled from the [[UA1 experiment]] producing 0.2 T uniform horizontal field and instrumented with scintillator planes constituting the Side Muon Range Detector.\n\n====Pi Zero detector====\n\nThe Pi-Zero ({{SubatomicParticle|Pion0}}) Detector (P0D) contains 40 plastic scintillator module planes, which in the central part are interleaved with 2.8 cm thick bags fillable of water and thick brass sheets, and in two peripheral regions scintillator modules are sandwiched with lead sheets. By comparison of the amount of interaction between modes with and without water in the bags, it is possible to extract the number of neutrino interactions occurring on the water - the target material inside the far detector Super-Kamiokande.\nThe size of the entire active P0D volume is around 2.1 m \u00d7 2.2 m \u00d7 2.4 m (X\u00d7Y\u00d7Z) and its mass with and without water is 15.8 and 12.9 tons respectively.\n\nThe main goal of the Pi-Zero Detector is measurement neutral [[pion]]s production in [[neutral current]] neutrino interactions on water:\n: {{SubatomicParticle|Muon neutrino}} + N \u2192 {{SubatomicParticle|Muon neutrino}} + N\u2019 + {{SubatomicParticle|Pion0}}\nThis reaction can mimic electron neutrino interactions because photons from pi0 decay can be mis-reconstructed as an electron in the Super-Kamiokande detector, thus this reaction can mimic electron neutrino interactions and constitute an important background in electron neutrino appearance measurement.\n<ref>{{cite journal |author=S. Assylbekov et all |title=The T2K ND280 off-axis pi\u2013zero detector |journal=Nuclear Instruments and Methods in Physics Research Section A: Accelerators, Spectrometers, Detectors and Associated Equipment |date=September 2012 |volume=686 |pages=48\u201363 |doi=10.1016/j.nima.2012.05.028|arxiv=1111.5030}}</ref>\n\n====Time projection chambers====\n\nThree [[time projection chamber]]s (TPCs) are gas-tight rectangular boxes, with a cathode plane in the centre and readout [[MicroMegas detector|MicroMegas]] modules at both sides parallel to the cathode. TPCs are filled with argon-based drift gas under atmospheric pressure. Charged particles crossing TPC ionise the gas along their track. The ionisation electrons drift from the cathode to the sides of the TPC, where they are detected by the MicroMegas providing a 3D image of a path of the traversing charged particle. Y and Z coordinates are based on the position of the detected ionisation electrons on the MicroMegas modules, and X coordinate is based on the electrons drift time. In the magnetic field, the curvature of this path allows to determine [[electric charge|charge]] and [[momentum]] of the particle, and the amount of the ionisation electrons per unit distance is used to identify particles based on the [[Bethe formula|Bethe-Bloch formula]].<ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K ND280 TPC collaboration |title=Time projection chambers for the T2K near detectors |journal=Nuclear Instruments and Methods in Physics Research Section A: Accelerators, Spectrometers, Detectors and Associated Equipment |date=May 2011 |volume=637 |issue=1 |pages=25\u201346 |doi=10.1016/j.nima.2011.02.036|arxiv=1012.0865}}</ref>\n\n====Fine-grained detectors====\n\nTwo fine-grained detectors (FGDs) are placed after the first and second TPCs. Together the FGDs and TPCs make up the tracker of ND280. The FGDs provide the active target mass for the neutrino interactions and are able to measure the short tracks of proton recoil. The first FGD is composed of scintillator layers only, while the second FGD is composed of alternating layers of scintillator and water. The second FGD is partially composed of water because the detector at Super-Kamiokande is water-based. Cross sections on carbon and on the water can be determined from a comparison of neutrino interactions in the two FGDs.\n\n====Electromagnetic Calorimeter====\n\nThe Electromagnetic Calorimeter (ECAL) surrounds the inner detectors (P0D, TPCs, FGDs) and consists of scintillator layers sandwiched with lead absorber sheets. Its role is to detect neutral particles, especially photons, and measure their energy and direction, as well as to detect charged particles providing additional information relevant for their identification.\n\n====Side Muon Range Detector====\n\nThe Side Muon Range Detector (SMRD) consists of scintillator modules which are inserted into the gaps in the magnet. The SMRD records muons escaping the inner parts of the detector at large angles with respect to the beam direction. It can also act as a trigger for [[cosmic rays]]. Finally, it can help identify beam interactions in the surrounding walls and in the magnet itself.\n\n==Super-Kamiokande==\n{{main|Super-Kamiokande}}\n\nSuper-Kamiokande detector is located 1000 m underground in the Mozumi Mine, under Mount Ikeno in the Kamoka area of Hida city. It is a [[stainless steel]] [[cylinder|cylindrical]] tank of about 40 m height and diameter, filled with 50,000 tons of [[water]] and instrumented with around 13,000 [[photomultiplier]] tubes (PMT). It detects a [[cone]] of [[Cherenkov radiation|Cherenkov light]] emitted by charged particles moving in water faster than light in this medium.\nIts goal is to measure [[muon]]s and [[electron]]s produced in [[charged current]] quasielastic interactions (CCQE) of {{SubatomicParticle|Muon neutrino}} and {{SubatomicParticle|Electron neutrino}}, respectively. Due to relatively large mass, muons usually do not change their direction and thus produce a well-defined cone of Cherenkov light observed by PMTs as a clear, sharp ring. In contrast, electrons, because of smaller mass, are more susceptible to scattering and almost always produce electromagnetic [[particle shower|showers]], observed by PMTs as a ring with fuzzy edges. Neutrino energy is calculated based on the direction and energy of a charged [[lepton]] produced in the CCQE interaction. In this way, {{SubatomicParticle|Muon neutrino}} and {{SubatomicParticle|Electron neutrino}} spectra are determined, leading to the measurement of the [[neutrino oscillation|oscillation]] parameters relevant for muon neutrino disappearance and electron neutrino appearance.<ref name=\"t2knim\"/>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Kamioka Observatory]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==References==\n*{{cite journal\n |author=Yuichi Oyama\n |year=2006\n |title=Results from K2K and status of T2K\n |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=o5ByTrijMjAC&pg=PA112&lpg=PA112&dq=%22Results+from+K2K+and+status+of+T2K%22#v=onepage&q=%22Results%20from%20K2K%20and%20status%20of%20T2K%22&f=false\n |journal=[[Nuclear Science and Safety in Europe]]\n |volume=2006 |issue= |pages=113\u2013124\n |isbn=978-1-4020-4964-4\n |doi=10.1007/978-1-4020-4965-1_9\n |arxiv=hep-ex/0512041 \n|series=NATO Security through Science Series\n }}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.t2k-experiment.org/ Official T2K site]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20040130175750/http://www.phys.washington.edu/~superk/ Super-Kamiokande]\n\n{{Breakthrough Prize laureates}}\n{{Neutrino detectors}}\n\n[[Category:Accelerator neutrino experiments]]\n[[Category:Science and technology in Japan]]\n[[Category:CERN experiments]]\n", "text_old": "{{primary sources|date=September 2012}}\n\n'''T2K''' ('''[[T\u014dkai, Ibaraki|Tokai]] to [[Kamioka, Gifu|Kamioka]]''') is a [[particle physics]] experiment studying the [[neutrino oscillations|oscillations]] of the [[accelerator neutrinos]]. The experiment is conducted in [[Japan]] by the international cooperation of about 500 physicists and engineers with over 60 research institutions from several countries from [[Europe]], [[Asia]] and [[North America]] <ref name=\"t2knim\">{{cite web |title=The T2K experiment collaboration |url=https://t2k-experiment.org/t2k/collaboration/}}</ref> and it is a recognized [[CERN]] experiment (RE13) <ref>{{cite web |url=http://committees.web.cern.ch/rec/welcome.html|title=Recognized Experiments at CERN |website=The CERN Scientific Committees |publisher=CERN |access-date=20 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://greybook.cern.ch/greybook/experiment/detail?id=RE13 |title=RE13/T2K : The long-baseline neutrino experiment |website=The CERN Experimental Programme |publisher=CERN |access-date=20 January 2020}}</ref>.\n\nT2K was the first experiment which observed the appearance of [[electron neutrino]]s in [[muon neutrino]] [[particle beam|beam]] <ref>[http://press.cern/press-releases/2010/05/particle-chameleon-caught-act-changing Particle Chameleon Caught in the act of Changing], CERN press release</ref><ref name=\"1106.2822\">{{Cite journal|arxiv=1106.2822 |author1=T2K Collaboration |title=Indication of Electron Neutrino Appearance from an Accelerator-produced Off-axis Muon Neutrino Beam |journal=Physical Review Letters |volume=107 |issue=4 |pages=041801 |year=2011 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.107.041801 |pmid=21866992 |bibcode = 2011PhRvL.107d1801A }}</ref>, it also provided the world best measurement of oscillation parameter ''\u03b8''<sub>23</sub> <ref name=\"1403.1532\">{{Cite journal|arxiv=1403.1532 |author1=T2K Collaboration | title=Precise Measurement of the Neutrino Mixing Parameter \\theta_{23} from Muon Neutrino Disappearance in an Off-Axis Beam | journal=Phys. Rev. Lett. |volume=112 | pages=181801 |year=2014 | doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.112.181801 }}</ref> and a hint of a significant [[CP violation|matter-antimatter asymmetry]] in neutrino oscillations <ref>{{Cite journal|arxiv=1502.01550 |author1=T2K Collaboration | title=Measurements of neutrino oscillation in appearance and disappearance channels by the T2K experiment with 6.6\u00d710$^{20}$ protons on target | journal=Phys. Rev. |volume=D91 | pages=072010 |year=2015 | doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.91.072010 }}</ref><ref name=\"1910.03887\">{{Cite journal|arxiv=1910.03887 |author1=T2K Collaboration | title=Constraint on the Matter-Antimatter Symmetry-Violating Phase in Neutrino Oscillations |year=2019 }}</ref>. The measurement of the neutrino-antineutrino oscillation asymmetry may bring us closer to the explanation of the existence of our [[Baryon asymmetry|matter-dominated]] Universe.\n\nThe intense beam of muon neutrinos is produced in the [[J-PARC]] facility (Japan Proton Accelerator Research Complex) in Tokai on the east coast of Japan. The beam is directed towards the [[Super-Kamiokande]] far detector located  295 km away in [[Hida, Gifu|Hida]]-city [[Gifu prefecture|Gifu]]. The properties and composition of the neutrino flux are first measured by a system of near detectors located 280 m from the beam production place at the J-PARC site, and then again in the Super-Kamiokande detector. Comparison of the content of different neutrino flavours in these two locations allows measurement of the oscillations probability on the way between near and far detectors. Super-Kamiokande is able to detect interactions of both, muon and electron neutrinos, and thus measure the disappearance of muon neutrino flux, as well as electron neutrino appearance in the beam.\n\n==Physics program==\n\nT2K experiment was  proposed in 2003 with the following measurement goals <ref name=\"1106.1238\">{{Cite journal|author=T2K Collaboration |year=2011 |title=The T2K Experiment |journal=Nuclear Instruments and Methods in Physics Research Section A: Accelerators, Spectrometers, Detectors and Associated Equipment |volume=659 |pages=106 |arxiv=1106.1238 |doi=10.1016/j.nima.2011.06.067 |bibcode = 2011NIMPA.659..106T }}</ref>:\n* The discovery of the {{SubatomicParticle|Muon neutrino}} \u2192 {{SubatomicParticle|Electron neutrino}} oscillations, and thus the confirmation that the last unknown mixing angle ''\u03b8''<sub>13</sub> is not zero\n* precise measurement of the oscillation parameters \u0394''m''{{su|b=23|p=2}} and ''\u03b8''<sub>23</sub> via muon neutrino disappearance studies\n* Search for sterile neutrino oscillations, which cause be observed as a deficit of  neutral current neutrino interactions\n* Measurements of various interaction cross-sections for different types of neutrinos and targets in an energy range of few GeV\n\nSince the start of the data taking in 2010, the T2K experiment succeeded to provide a list of world-class results:\n* The confirmation of electron neutrino appearance in the muon neutrino beam ({{SubatomicParticle|Muon neutrino}}\u2192{{SubatomicParticle|Electron neutrino}}), which was the first time when neutrinos produced in one flavour was explicitly observed in another flavour. <ref name=\"1106.2822\" /><ref name=\"1304.0841\">{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=Evidence of electron neutrino appearance in a muon neutrino beam |journal=Physical Review D |date=5 August 2013 |volume=88 |issue=3 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.88.032002|arxiv=1304.0841}}</ref>\n* The most precise measurement of the ''\u03b8''<sub>23</sub> parameter. <ref name=\"1403.1532\" />\n* The first significant constraint on the ''\u03b4''<sub>CP</sub> parameter, responsible for the matter-antimatter asymmetry in the neutrino sector. <ref name=\"1910.03887\" />\n* Limits on a [[sterile neutrino]] oscillation parameters based on studies in the near ND280 <ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration | |title=Search for short baseline disappearance with the T2K near detector |journal=Physical Review D |date=16 March 2015 |volume=91 |issue=5 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.91.051102 |arxiv=1410.8811}}</ref> and far Super-Kamiokande <ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=Search for light sterile neutrinos with the T2K far detector Super-Kamiokande at a baseline of 295\u00a0km |journal=Physical Review D |date=30 April 2019 |volume=99 |issue=7 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.99.071103 |arxiv=1902.06529}}</ref> detectors.\n* Various cross-section measurements of electron<ref>{{cite journal | author=T2K Collaboration |title=Measurement of the charged-current electron (anti-)neutrino inclusive cross-sections at the T2K off-axis near detector ND280 |journal=arXiv:2002.11986 [hep-ex] |date=27 February 2020 | arxiv=2002.11986}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=Measurement of the electron neutrino charged-current interaction rate on water with the T2K ND280 pi0 detector |journal=Physical Review D |date=19 June 2015 |volume=91 |issue=11 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.91.112010}}</ref> and muon neutrino and antineutrino, including inclusive charged current (CC) interactions<ref>{{cite journal | author=T2K Collaboration |title=Measurement of the inclusive numu charged current cross section on carbon in the near detector of the T2K experiment |journal=Physical Review D |date=7 May 2013 |volume=87 |issue=9 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.87.092003|arxiv=1302.4908}}</ref>, CC interactions without pions <ref>{{cite journal | author=T2K Collaboration | |title=Measurement of double-differential muon neutrino charged-current interactions on C8H8 without pions in the final state using the T2K off-axis beam |journal=Physical Review D |date=21 June 2016 |volume=93 |issue=11 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.93.112012|arxiv=1602.03652}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration|title=Measurement of the numu charged-current quasielastic cross section on carbon with the ND280 detector at T2K |journal=Physical Review D |date=11 December 2015 |volume=92 |issue=11 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.92.112003|arxiv=1411.6264}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=First combined measurement of the muon neutrino and antineutrino charged-current cross section without pions in the final state at T2K |journal=arXiv:2002.09323 [hep-ex] |date=21 February 2020 |arxiv=2002.09323}}</ref> and with single pion in the final state<ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=First measurement of the muon neutrino charged current single pion production cross section on water with the T2K near detector |journal=Physical Review D |date=26 January 2017 |volume=95 |issue=1 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.95.012010|arxiv=1605.07964}}</ref>, coherent pion production<ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=Measurement of Coherent pi+ Production in Low Energy Neutrino-Carbon Scattering |journal=Physical Review Letters |date=4 November 2016 |volume=117 |issue=19 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.117.192501|arxiv=1604.04406}}</ref>, neutral current interactions<ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=Measurement of the neutrino-oxygen neutral-current interaction cross section by observing nuclear deexcitation gamma rays |journal=Physical Review D |date=31 October 2014 |volume=90 |issue=7 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevD.90.072012|arxiv=1403.3140}}</ref>, etc. on different targets such as carbon, water and iron<ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=Measurement of the muon neutrino charged-current cross sections on water, hydrocarbon and iron, and their ratios, with the T2K on-axis detectors |journal=Progress of Theoretical and Experimental Physics |date=September 2019 |volume=2019 |issue=9 |doi=10.1093/ptep/ptz070}}</ref>.\n\nFuture upgrades to T2K is expected to provide further constrain on the ''\u03b4''<sub>CP</sub> phase by comparing oscillations of neutrinos to those of antineutrinos, as well as more precise measurements of \u0394''m''{{su|b=23|p=2}} and ''\u03b8''<sub>23</sub> parameters, and cross-section measurements which will extend our understanding of neutrino interactions and thus improve theoretical models used in neutrino generators.<ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=Proposal for an Extended Run of T2K to $20\\times10^{21}$ POT |journal=arXiv:1609.04111 [hep-ex, physics:physics] |date=13 September 2016 |arxiv=1609.04111}}</ref><ref name=\"1805.04163\">{{cite journal |author=Hyper-Kamiokande Collaboration |title=Hyper-Kamiokande Design Report |journal=arXiv:1805.04163 [astro-ph, physics:hep-ex, physics:physics] |date=28 November 2018 |arxiv=1805.04163}}</ref>\n\n==Neutrino beam==\n\n[[File:The entire view of J-PARC.jpg|thumb|Bird's-eye view of the entire facility]]\n[[File:Superconducting Magnets J-PARC.jpg|thumb|Superconducting magnets under construction in 2008 to veer the proton beam to the direction of Kamioka]]\n[[File:J-PARC Neutrino Experiment Facility Primary Beamline Final Focusing Section.jpg|thumb|Final stage of the proton beam line before target to generate neutrino beam]]\nT2K uses a muon neutrino or muon antineutrino [[accelerator neutrino|beam]] produced at the [[J-PARC]] facility using a proton beam gradually accelerated to 30 GeV by a system of three [[particle accelerator|accelerators]]: first to 400 MeV energy by the Linac linear accelerator, then up to 3 GeV by the RCS (Rapid Cycle Synchrotron), and finally up to 30 GeV by the MR [[synchrotron]] (Main Ring). [[Proton]]s collide with a [[graphite]] target, producing [[meson]]s, mainly [[pion]]s and [[kaon]]s, which are then focused by a set of three [[magnetic horn]]s and directed into a tunnel called the decay volume. Depending on the horns polarity, either positive or negative particles are focused. Positive pions and kaons decay mainly into {{SubatomicParticle|Muon+}} and {{SubatomicParticle|Muon neutrino}}, forming a muon neutrino beam, while negative pions and kaons decay mainly into {{SubatomicParticle|Muon-}} and {{SubatomicParticle|Muon antineutrino}}, forming a muon antineutrino beam. All remaining [[hadron]]s and charged [[lepton]]s are stopped by a 75-ton block of graphite (so-called beam dump) and in the ground, while neutrinos travel underground towards the far detector.<ref name=\"t2knim\"/>\n\n===Off-axis beam===\n\nT2K is the first experiment in which the concept of off-axis [[accelerator neutrino|neutrino beam]] was realized. The neutrino beam at J-PARC is designed so that it can be directed 2 to 3 [[degree (angle)|degrees]] away from the [[Super-Kamiokande]] far detector and one of the near detectors, ND280. The off-axis angle was chosen to 2.5\u00b0 to maximize the probability of oscillation at a distance corresponding to the far detector, which for 295&nbsp;km is maximal for around 600&nbsp;MeV neutrinos. In this neutrino energy range, the dominant type of neutrino interactions are charged current quasielastic interactions, for which it is possible to reconstruct the energy of the interacting neutrino only on the basis of the momentum and direction of the produced charged lepton. The higher neutrino energies are suppressed by the off-axis configuration, decreasing the number of interactions with meson production, which are background in the oscillation analysis in the T2K experiment.<ref name=\"t2knim\"/><ref name=\"t2kflux\">{{cite journal |author=T2K Collaboration |title=T2K neutrino flux prediction |journal=Physical Review D |date=2 January 2013 |volume=87 |issue=1 |doi=10.1103/physrevd.87.012001|arxiv=1211.0469}}</ref>\n\n==Near detectors==\n\nThe near detector complex is located at a distance of 280 meters from the graphite target. Its purpose is to measure the neutrino flux before oscillations and to study neutrino interactions. The system consists of three main detectors:\n* INGRID detector (Interactive Neutrino GRID) located on the axis of the neutrino beam,\n* ND280 detector located 2.5\u00b0 away from the beam axis, i.e. at the same angle as the far detector.\n* Wagasci-BabyMIND is a magnetised neutrino detector located at 1.5\u00b0 off-axis angle, built to explore the energy spectrum variation with the off-axis angle and cross-sections at higher average neutrino energy.\n\n===Signal readout===\n\nExcept for the Time Projection Chambres in ND280, the entire active material (enabling particle tracking) of the near detectors is plastic scintillator. The light produced by traversing particles in the plastic [[scintillator]] bars and planes is collected by wavelength-shifting fibres and detected by Hamamatsu Multi-pixel photon counters installed/located at one or both ends of the fibres. Scintillator bars are organised into layers, where bars in two neighbouring layers are perpendicular to each other providing together 3D information about traversing particles.\n\n===INGRID detector===\n\nThe main purpose of the INGRID detector is the monitoring of the direction and intensity of the beam on a daily basis by direct detection of neutrino interactions. The INGRID detector consists of 16 identical modules arranged in the shape of a cross, 7 in a vertical and 7 in a horizontal arm, plus 2 modules outside the cross. Height and width of the arms are 10 meters. A single module consists of alternating layers of iron and a plastic scintillator. An additional 4 veto layers of the scintillator surround the module on the sides to distinguish particles entering from the outside from those produced by interactions inside the module. The total mass of iron in one module is 7.1 tons and constitutes 96% of the module weight. On the neutrino beam axis, in the middle of the cross between the vertical and horizontal arm, there is an additional module built only from layers of the plastic scintillator (Proton Module) with a mass of 0.55 tons. Its purpose is to register quasielastic interactions and compare the obtained results with the simulations.\n\n===ND280 detector===\n\n[[File:J-PARC T2K ND280 Pit.jpg|thumb|ND280 under construction]]\nThe ND280 detector is used to measure the flux, energy spectrum and electron neutrino beam pollution for the same off-axis angle as for the far detector. ND280 also investigates various types of muon and electron neutrino and antineutrino interactions. All this allows estimating the expected number and type of interactions in the far detector, reducing the systematic error in the neutrino oscillations analysis associated with models of neutrino interactions and flux.\n\nND280 is composed of the set of inner sub-detectors: Pi-Zero detector and a tracker with 2 Fine-Grained Detectors interleaved with 3 Time Projection Chambres, placed inside of a metal frame called a basket. The basket is surrounded by the electromagnetic calorimeter and a magnet recycled from the [[UA1 experiment]] producing 0.2 T uniform horizontal field and instrumented with scintillator planes constituting the Side Muon Range Detector.\n\n====Pi Zero detector====\n\nThe Pi-Zero ({{SubatomicParticle|Pion0}}) Detector (P0D) contains 40 plastic scintillator module planes, which in the central part are interleaved with 2.8 cm thick bags fillable of water and thick brass sheets, and in two peripheral regions scintillator modules are sandwiched with lead sheets. By comparison of the amount of interaction between modes with and without water in the bags, it is possible to extract the number of neutrino interactions occurring on the water - the target material inside the far detector Super-Kamiokande.\nThe size of the entire active P0D volume is around 2.1 m \u00d7 2.2 m \u00d7 2.4 m (X\u00d7Y\u00d7Z) and its mass with and without water is 15.8 and 12.9 tons respectively.\n\nThe main goal of the Pi-Zero Detector is measurement neutral [[pion]]s production in [[neutral current]] neutrino interactions on water:\n: {{SubatomicParticle|Muon neutrino}} + N \u2192 {{SubatomicParticle|Muon neutrino}} + N\u2019 + {{SubatomicParticle|Pion0}}\nThis reaction can mimic electron neutrino interactions because photons from pi0 decay can be mis-reconstructed as an electron in the Super-Kamiokande detector, thus this reaction can mimic electron neutrino interactions and constitute an important background in electron neutrino appearance measurement.\n<ref>{{cite journal |author=S. Assylbekov et all |title=The T2K ND280 off-axis pi\u2013zero detector |journal=Nuclear Instruments and Methods in Physics Research Section A: Accelerators, Spectrometers, Detectors and Associated Equipment |date=September 2012 |volume=686 |pages=48\u201363 |doi=10.1016/j.nima.2012.05.028|arxiv=1111.5030}}</ref>\n\n====Time projection chambers====\n\nThree [[time projection chamber]]s (TPCs) are gas-tight rectangular boxes, with a cathode plane in the centre and readout [[MicroMegas detector|MicroMegas]] modules at both sides parallel to the cathode. TPCs are filled with argon-based drift gas under atmospheric pressure. Charged particles crossing TPC ionise the gas along their track. The ionisation electrons drift from the cathode to the sides of the TPC, where they are detected by the MicroMegas providing a 3D image of a path of the traversing charged particle. Y and Z coordinates are based on the position of the detected ionisation electrons on the MicroMegas modules, and X coordinate is based on the electrons drift time. In the magnetic field, the curvature of this path allows to determine [[electric charge|charge]] and [[momentum]] of the particle, and the amount of the ionisation electrons per unit distance is used to identify particles based on the [[Bethe formula|Bethe-Bloch formula]].<ref>{{cite journal |author=T2K ND280 TPC collaboration |title=Time projection chambers for the T2K near detectors |journal=Nuclear Instruments and Methods in Physics Research Section A: Accelerators, Spectrometers, Detectors and Associated Equipment |date=May 2011 |volume=637 |issue=1 |pages=25\u201346 |doi=10.1016/j.nima.2011.02.036|arxiv=1012.0865}}</ref>\n\n====Fine-grained detectors====\n\nTwo fine-grained detectors (FGDs) are placed after the first and second TPCs. Together the FGDs and TPCs make up the tracker of ND280. The FGDs provide the active target mass for the neutrino interactions and are able to measure the short tracks of proton recoil. The first FGD is composed of scintillator layers only, while the second FGD is composed of alternating layers of scintillator and water. The second FGD is partially composed of water because the detector at Super-Kamiokande is water-based. Cross sections on carbon and on the water can be determined from a comparison of neutrino interactions in the two FGDs.\n\n====Electromagnetic Calorimeter====\n\nThe Electromagnetic Calorimeter (ECAL) surrounds the inner detectors (P0D, TPCs, FGDs) and consists of scintillator layers sandwiched with lead absorber sheets. Its role is to detect neutral particles, especially photons, and measure their energy and direction, as well as to detect charged particles providing additional information relevant for their identification.\n\n====Side Muon Range Detector====\n\nThe Side Muon Range Detector (SMRD) consists of scintillator modules which are inserted into the gaps in the magnet. The SMRD records muons escaping the inner parts of the detector at large angles with respect to the beam direction. It can also act as a trigger for [[cosmic rays]]. Finally, it can help identify beam interactions in the surrounding walls and in the magnet itself.\n\n==Super-Kamiokande==\n{{main|Super-Kamiokande}}\n\nSuper-Kamiokande detector is located 1000 m underground in the Mozumi Mine, under Mount Ikeno in the Kamoka area of Hida city. It is a [[stainless steel]] [[cylinder|cylindrical]] tank of about 40 m height and diameter, filled with 50,000 tons of [[water]] and instrumented with around 13,000 [[photomultiplier]] tubes (PMT). It detects a [[cone]] of [[Cherenkov radiation|Cherenkov light]] emitted by charged particles moving in water faster than light in this medium.\nIts goal is to measure [[muon]]s and [[electron]]s produced in [[charged current]] quasielastic interactions (CCQE) of {{SubatomicParticle|Muon neutrino}} and {{SubatomicParticle|Electron neutrino}}, respectively. Due to relatively large mass, muons usually do not change their direction and thus produce a well-defined cone of Cherenkov light observed by PMTs as a clear, sharp ring. In contrast, electrons, because of smaller mass, are more susceptible to scattering and almost always produce electromagnetic [[particle shower|showers]], observed by PMTs as a ring with fuzzy edges. Neutrino energy is calculated based on the direction and energy of a charged [[lepton]] produced in the CCQE interaction. In this way, {{SubatomicParticle|Muon neutrino}} and {{SubatomicParticle|Electron neutrino}} spectra are determined, leading to the measurement of the [[neutrino oscillation|oscillation]] parameters relevant for muon neutrino disappearance and electron neutrino appearance.<ref name=\"t2knim\"/>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Kamioka Observatory]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==References==\n*{{cite journal\n |author=Yuichi Oyama\n |year=2006\n |title=Results from K2K and status of T2K\n |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=o5ByTrijMjAC&pg=PA112&lpg=PA112&dq=%22Results+from+K2K+and+status+of+T2K%22#v=onepage&q=%22Results%20from%20K2K%20and%20status%20of%20T2K%22&f=false\n |journal=[[Nuclear Science and Safety in Europe]]\n |volume=2006 |issue= |pages=113\u2013124\n |isbn=978-1-4020-4964-4\n |doi=10.1007/978-1-4020-4965-1_9\n |arxiv=hep-ex/0512041 \n|series=NATO Security through Science Series\n }}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.t2k-experiment.org/ Official T2K site]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20040130175750/http://www.phys.washington.edu/~superk/ Super-Kamiokande]\n\n{{Breakthrough Prize laureates}}\n{{Neutrino detectors}}\n\n[[Category:Accelerator neutrino experiments]]\n[[Category:Science and technology in Japan]]\n[[Category:CERN experiments]]\n", "name_user": "Batmann", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePhysics program:wiki link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/T2K_experiment"}
{"title_page": "Actors of the Com\u00e9die-Fran\u00e7aise", "text_new": "{{italic title}}\n{{Expand French|Les Acteurs de la Com\u00e9die-Fran\u00e7aise|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox artwork\n| image_file = File:Antoine_Watteau_062.jpg\n| title = Coquettes qui pour voir \n| other_title_1 = Actors of the Com\u00e9die-Fran\u00e7aise\n| image_size = 240px\n| artist = [[Jean-Antoine Watteau]]\n| year = Between 1711\u20131717\n| material = [[panel painting|oil on panel]]\n| height_metric = 20\n| width_metric = 25\n| city = [[Saint Petersburg]]\n| museum = [[Hermitage Museum|The Hermitage]]\n| accession = \u0413\u042d-1131\n}}\n'''''Coquettes qui pour voir''''' is the name commonly given to an [[Panel painting|oil on panel]] painting in the [[Hermitage Museum]] in [[Saint Petersburg]], by French artist [[Jean-Antoine Watteau]], the leading painter of the [[R\u00e9gence]] era and a pioneer of the [[Rococo]] style. Completed in the 1710s, it was a part of the collections formed by Parisian merchant and art collector [[Pierre Crozat]], and later by his relatives. Since being acquired for [[Catherine II of Russia]] in 1772, the painting was held among the Russian imperial family collections in the Hermitage and, after the 1850s, in the [[Gatchina Palace]]; in 1920, it was transitioned in the Winter Palace, where it currently remains as part of the Hermitage Museum permanent exhibition. Throughout its provenance, the work has also been known under a number of various titles, with ''Coquettes...'' becoming dominant since the later 19th century; in Russian literature, a title of '''''Actors of the Com\u00e9die-Fran\u00e7aise'''''{{efn|{{lang-ru|\u00ab\u0410\u043a\u0442\u0451\u0440\u044b \u0444\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0443\u0437\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0435\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0430\u00bb}}}} has been adopted since the later 20th century, following studies of Watteau's drawings that established a possible identity.\n\nThe painting is a group portrait which is considered to be the rarest kind in Watteau's body of work; it depicts five figures in half-length \u2014 two men, two women and a [[Black people|black]] boy \u2014 set amidst a dark background. Among various explanations of the subject, one is accepted in Russia that identifies the adults as members of the [[Com\u00e9die-Fran\u00e7aise]] who performed in [[Florent Carton Dancourt]]'s play ''[[The Three Cousins]]'', and the black boy as Pierre Crozat's servant; other scholars presumed it to be a depiction of [[commedia dell'arte masks]] or of a family group preparing for a ball.\n\n==Description==\n===Composition===\n{{quote box|align=left|width=25%|quote=\"\u2026Watteau combines portraiture with a striking feeling for the picturesque. The rounded, resilient brushstrokes seem to have benn applied with the lightness of spontaneous improvisation, yet at the same time with a bold precision which only a mature master could command. The faces, showing fatigue, animation and faint anxiety, are illuminated by a mysterious theatrical light, the fantastic costumes shimmer with wine-pink tones against the black velvet of the masks. All this creates an impression of the natural unity of the imagined and the actual, a [[E. T. A. Hoffmann|Hoffmannesque]] world where the characters\u2019 reality in only enhanced by the strangeness of their surroundings.\"|source=\u2014[[Mikhail German]] on ''Actors...'', in a 1980 artbook ''Antoine Watteau''.{{sfn|German|1980|p=8}}}}\n''Actors ...'' is an oil on panel painting upholstered in wood, and measures approximately 20 \u00d7 25&nbsp;cm.{{sfnm|Nemilova|1964|1p=181|2a1=Grasselli|2a2=Rosenberg|2a3=Parmantier|1984|2p=311}}\n\nIn the painting, Watteau depicts five figures in half-length, standing around a stone balustrade. To the right, an outwardly old man stands upon a stick and holds a mushroom hat, dressed in a skullcap. By the balustrade's other side, a young girl is shown in a light-colored striped dress with high standing collar, standing behind a black boy in green-striped clothes. Over the girl's shoulder, a man's head appears in a large motley beret. To the left side, a young woman turned to the right in profile, appears in a Polish-styled red dress and white chipper, leaning on the balustrade and holding a black mask in the right hand.{{sfn|Nemilova|1964|p=181}}\n\nDefects found on the panel include a restored crack to the right of the old man's cape; gaps in shadows, more importantly at the bottom edge and around the girl's head; chippings painted over the girl's left shoulder.{{sfn|Nemilova|1964|p=181}} An X-ray analysis published by Soviet scholars in 1973 revealed changes in the composition showing that in the early stages the woman at the left was bareheaded, wore a different costume, and had placed her mask on the balustrade. The several differences between the painting and the engraving, notably in the coiffure of the central female figure, are considered relating to the state of the painting, which has been somewhat damaged and restored in the past.{{sfnm|Zolotov|1973|1p=138|Nemilova|1982|2pp=130\u2013131|3a1=Grasselli|3a2=Rosenberg|3a3=Parmantier|3y=1984|3p=312}}\n\n<!--[[Donald Posner]] described ''Actors'' less successful in its idea and composition, while having beautiful painting of individual forms.{{sfn|Posner|1984|p=290}}-->\n\n===Identity of subjects===\n[[File:Henri Simon Thomassin - Coquettes qui pour voir galans au rendez-vous.jpg|thumb|The painting's traditional naming originates from {{Interlanguage link|Henri Simon Thomassin|lt=Henri Simon Thomassin's|fr}} engraving, executed for the ''Recueil Jullienne''.]]\nUntil the middle of the 20th century, sources and studies on Watteau variously defined the work's subject. In notes to [[Pellegrino Antonio Orlandi]]'s ''Abecedario pittorico'', [[Pierre-Jean Mariette]] referred the work to as ''Coquettes qui pour voir galans au rendez vous'' ({{trans|\"Coquettish women, who to meet gallant men go around...\"}}), after the first verses of quatrains accompanying Thomassin's engraving for the ''Recueil Jullienne''; Mariette thought the panel depicts \"people in disguise for a ball, among whom is one dressed as an old man.\"<ref name=\"Dacier & Co\">{{cite book|first=\u00c9mile|last=Dacier|first2=Albert|last2=Vuaflart|title=Jean de Julienne et les graveurs de Watteau au XVIII-e si\u00e8cle. III. Catalogue|date=1922|location=Paris|language=fr|publisher=M. Rousseau|page=23}}</ref> [[Fran\u00e7ois-Bernard L\u00e9pici\u00e9]] refers to the composition as ''Retour de Bal'' in a 1741 obituary of {{Interlanguage link|Henri Simon Thomassin|fr}}, believing the figures to be returning from a ball;<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=L\u00e9pici\u00e9|first=F. B.|date=March 1741|title=Lettre sur la mort de M. Thomassin|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CZJQAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA568#v=onepage&q&f=false|journal=Mercure de France|pages=568\u2013570|via=[[Google Books]]|language=fr}}</ref>{{rp|569}}{{sfn|Camesasca|1971|p=115|loc=cat. no. 162}} in contrary, ''Catalogue Crozat'' (1755) and [[Dezallier d'Argenville#Antoine-Nicolas Dezallier d'Argenville|Antoine-Nicolas Dezallier d'Argenville]] described it as a depiction of masked figures preparing for a ball.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Catalogue des tableaux du cabinet de M. Crozat Baron de Thi\u00e8res \u00e1 Paris|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=L9DJyvbqgKcC&pg=PA65|year=1755|language=fr|location=Paris|page=65|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Voyage Pictoresque de Paris|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6aZfAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA140#v=onepage&q&f=false|last=Dezallier d'Argenville|first=Antoine-Nicolas|year=1757|location=Paris|page=140|orig-year=1749|language=fr|via=Google Books|quote=Des personnages en masque se pr\u00e9parant pour le bal, par Watteau. Il y en a une estampe grav\u00e9e par Thomassin.}}</ref>\n\nLater sources, more prominently in France and Russia, similarly had various definitions on the subject: {{Interlanguage link|Johann Ernst von Munnich|ru|\u041c\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0445, \u0418\u043e\u0433\u0430\u043d\u043d \u042d\u0440\u043d\u0441\u0442}} refers to the work as ''Personnages en masques'' ({{trans|\"Characters in Masks\"}}) in the two-volume catalogue of the Hermitage collection;<ref>{{Cite book|title=Catalogue raisonn\u00e9 des tableaux qui trouvent dans les Galeries et Cabinets du Palais Imp\u00e9rial \u00e0 Saint-P\u00e9tersbourg|last=Munnich|first=Johann Ersnt von|date=1773\u20131783|volume=1|page=274|language=fr|postscript=. Cat. no. 873.}}</ref> the Hermitage's 1797 catalogue features the title ''The Mascarade'',<ref>{{cite book|title=\u041a\u0430\u0442\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043c, \u0445\u0440\u0430\u043d\u044f\u0449\u0438\u043c\u0441\u044f \u0432 \u0418\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0413\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0435 \u042d\u0440\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0436\u0430|editor-last=Labensky|editor-first=F. I.|trans-title=Catalogue of Paintings housed in the Imperial Hermitage Gallery|year=1797|language=ru|volume=2|page=55|postscript=. Cat. no. 2545.}}</ref> whereas the 1859 inventory registry features only the work's description\u2014\"two women, talking with two men, and a negro beside them\".<ref>{{cite book|title=\u041e\u043f\u0438\u0441\u044c \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043c \u0438 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u0444\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043c, \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0449\u0438\u043c \u0432 \u0437\u0430\u0432\u0435\u0434\u044b\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0438 II \u043e\u0442\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0418\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u042d\u0440\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0436\u0430|trans-title=Inventory of paintings and plafonds in the office of the Second Department of the Imperial Hermitage Museum|language=ru|year=1859|postscript=. Cat. no. 1699}}</ref>{{sfnm|Nemilova|1964|1pp=81, 181|Nemilova|1970|2pp=145\u2013146|Nemilova|1989|3p=133}} In his writings, {{Interlanguage link|Pierre Edmond Alexandre H\u00e9douin|lt=Edmond H\u00e9douin|fr|Pierre Edmond Alexandre H\u00e9douin}} referred the work to as ''Le Rendez-vous du bal masqu\u00e9'',{{sfn|Hedouin|1856|loc=cat. no. 30|p=97}} before [[Edmond de Goncourt]]'s ''Catalogue raisonn\u00e9...'' introduced the Mariette-mentioned title into common use.{{sfnm|1a1=Grasselli|1a2=Rosenberg|1a3=Parmantier|1y=1984|1pp=312\u2013313|Eidelberg|2019|2ps=: \"Beginning with Edmond de Goncourt, it has become customary to assign the painting the awkward name of ''Coquettes qui pour voir'', the opening words of the two quatrains that appears under the Thomassin engraving.\"}}\n\nEarly in the 1900s, the French author Virgile Josz presumed the work to be a depiction of [[commedia dell'arte masks]], with the old man as [[Pantalone]], the women as Rosaura and [[Isabella (commedia dell'arte)|Isabella]], and the young man as [[Scapino]];{{sfnm|Josz|1903|1pp=329\u2013330|Josz|1904|2p=146}} in later years, these points were adopted by a number of scholars{{efn|Virgile Josh\u2019s description of ''Coquettes...'' had been adopted by a number of scholars, including the Russians [[Alexandre Benois]],<ref name=\"Benois\">{{cite magazine|last=Benois|first=Alexandre|author-link=Alexandre Benois|title=\u0416\u0438\u0432\u043e\u043f\u0438\u0441\u044c \u044d\u043f\u043e\u0445\u0438 \u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u043a\u043a\u043e \u0438 \u0440\u043e\u043a\u043e\u043a\u043e|language=ru|trans-title=Painting in the Age of Baroque and Rococo|department=1908: \u0412\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u043d|work=\u0421\u0442\u0430\u0440\u044b\u0435 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u044b|pages=720\u2013734|date=November\u2013December 1908}}</ref>{{rp|729}} Valentin Miller,<ref name=\u201cgorod1923\u201d>{{cite book|last=Miller|first=V.|chapter=\u0424\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0443\u0437\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0436\u0438\u0432\u043e\u043f\u0438\u0441\u044c XVII-\u0433\u043e \u0438 XVIII-\u0433\u043e \u0432.\u0432. \u0432 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u0437\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0445 \u042d\u0440\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0436\u0430 (L\u2019art fran\u00e7ais du XVIII-i\u00e8me et du XVIII-i\u00e8me s.s. dans les nouvelles salles de l\u2019Ermitage)|trans-chapter=\u201cFrench Painting of the Seventeenth and Eighteenth Centuries in the New Rooms of the Hermitage\u201d|title=\u0413\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434: \u043b\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430, \u0438\u0441\u043a\u0443\u0441\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e|location=\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433|publisher=\u0413\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0410\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0438\u0437\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430|year=1923|pages=52\u201378}}</ref>{{rp|58\u201359}} and {{Interlanguage link|Sergei Ersnt|ru|\u042d\u0440\u043d\u0441\u0442, \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}},<ref name=Ersnt>{{Cite magazine|last=Ernst|first=Serge|author-link=Sergei Ernst|date=March 1928|title=L\u2019exposition de peinture fran\u00e7aise des XVIIe et XVIIIe siecles au mus\u00e9e de l\u2019Ermitage, a Petrograd (1922\u20131925)|url=https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k61112882/f191.image.r=watteau|magazine=[[Gazette des Beaux-Arts]]|volume=17|issue=785|language=fr|pages=163\u2013182|access-date=March 29, 2019|via=[[Gallica]]}}</ref>{{rp|172\u2013173}} as well as the Hermitage Museum's 1958 catalogue of the painting collection.<ref>{{Cite book|title=\u0413\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u042d\u0440\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0436. \u041e\u0442\u0434\u0435\u043b \u0437\u0430\u043f\u0430\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0435\u0432\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0435\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0438\u0441\u043a\u0443\u0441\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430: \u041a\u0430\u0442\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433 \u0436\u0438\u0432\u043e\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438|publisher=Iskusstvo|year=1958|editor-last=Levinson-Lessing|editor-first=V. F.|volume=1|location=Leningrad, Moscow|page=270|language=ru|trans-title=The State Hermitage Museum. The Department for Western European Art: Catalog of Paintings}}</ref>}} Josz's contemporary {{Interlanguage link|Louis de Fourcaud|fr}} considered figures to be \"a family group dressed for an elegant masquerade,\" painted after material from sketchbooks.<ref name=\"Fourcaud\">{{cite magazine|first=Louis de|last=Fourcaud|title=Antoine Watteau: scenes et figures th\u00e9atrales (I)|url=https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k4325209/f150.image|language=fr|work=La Revue de l'art ancien et moderne|date=February 1904|volume=15|issue=83|pages=135\u2013150|access-date=March 31, 2019|via=Gallica}}</ref>{{rp|144}}{{sfnm|Nemilova|1964|1pp=81, 181|Nemilova|1970|2pp=145\u2013147|3a1=Grasselli|3a2=Rosenberg|3a3=Parmantier|3y=1984|3p=312|Nemilova|1989|4p=133}}\n\nIn her monograph on Watteau published in 1950, Helene Adhemar identified the woman in red as [[Charlotte Desmares]], a leading actress of the [[Com\u00e9die-Fran\u00e7aise]] during the 1700s and the 1710s and once a mistress of [[Philippe II, Duke of Orl\u00e9ans]];{{sfn|Adhemar|1950|p=119}} Adhemar's point was furthered in [[Karl Parker]] and Jacques Mathey's 1957\u20131958 catalogue of Watteau drawings; they concluded that the old man could be another Com\u00e9die-Fran\u00e7aise player, Pierre Le Noir.{{efn|Pierre Le Noir (1657\u20131731) was a son of [[La Thorilli\u00e8re|Fran\u00e7ois Le Noir ''dit'' La Thorilli\u00e8re]], a prominent actor associated with [[Moli\u00e8re]]\u2019s [[Moli\u00e8re's company|company]]. He joined the royal troupe in 1671, first as a touring artist; in 1684, Le Noir became a ''[[Soci\u00e9taires of the Com\u00e9die-Fran\u00e7aise|soci\u00e9taire]]'' of the Com\u00e9die-Fran\u00e7aise. Le Noir, also known as La Thorilli\u00e8re like his father was, mostly performed ''a manteau'' roles.{{sfnm|1a1=Grasselli|1a2=Rosenberg|1a3=Parmantier|1y=1984|1p=478|Nemilova|1989|2p=140}}}} In the Soviet Union, the Hermitage staff member Inna Nemilova supported these points, and also concluded the young man to be [[Philippe Poisson (actor)|Philippe Poisson]].{{sfn|Belova|2006|pp=58\u201359}}{{sfnm|Zolotov|1973|1p=139|Nemilova|1982|2pp=131\u2013133|Nemilova|1989|3pp=137\u2013138, 140, 142, 144, 146}} In addition, Nemilova pointed out Desmares could be possibly depicted by Watteau in both versions of ''[[The Embarkation for Cythera]]'', and also other canvas{{efn|These include ''The Island of Cythera'' (''The Embarkation''\u2019s preceding work, now in the [[St\u00e4del Museum]] in Frankfurt), ''The Dreamer'' (now in the [[Art Institute of Chicago]]), ''The Polish Woman'' (now in the [[National Museum, Warsaw|National Museum in Warsaw]]), and the lost ''La Polonnoise'' engraved by {{Interlanguage link|Michel Aubert|lt=Michel Aubert|fr}}.}} and various drawings.{{sfn|Nemilova|1964|pp=86\u201387, 91}}\n<!--In a 1980 biography of Watteau, Mikhail German was sceptical of Nemilova's point; he said he \"would like to believe this lady is really the actress Christine Desmares,\" and is not \"going to insist the man to the right is really [...] La Thorilli\u00e8re.\"{{sfn|German|2010|loc=chapter X|p=105}}-->\n\n===Authorship and dating===\nWatteau's authorship of the panel has never been seriously questioned by scholars until the early 20th century, when {{Interlanguage link|Nicolas Wrangel (art historian)|lt=Nicolas Wrangel|ru|\u0412\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0433\u0435\u043b\u044c, \u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\u0439 \u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}} considered it a work by [[Philippe Mercier]] in a 1912 letter to his German colleague Ernst Heinrich Zimmermann; the latter chose to classify it among the \"doubtful pictures;\"<ref>{{Cite book|title=Watteau: des Meisters Werke in 182 Abbildungen|last=Zimmermann|first=E. Heinrich|publisher=Deutsche Verlags-Anstalt|year=1912|location=Stuttgart, Leipzig|pages=190\u2013191|language=de|author-link=Ernst Heinrich Zimmermann|series=Klassiker der Kunst|volume=21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Ettinger|first=P. D.|date=1912|title=Rossica|language=ru|magazine=[[Apollon (magazine)|Apollon]]|issue=7|pages=61\u201362|postscript=. [http://www.v-ivanov.it/apollon/apollon_1912_07.pdf See] a facsimile copy at the Vyacheslav Ivanov Research Center archive.}}</ref> similarly, [[Jean Ferr\u00e9]] included the work among \"attributed to Watteau.\"<ref>{{Cite book|title=Watteau|editor-last=Ferr\u00e9|editor-first=Jean|editor-link=Jean Ferr\u00e9|publisher=\u00c9ditions Athena|year=1972|volume=1|location=Madrid|pages=151\u2013152}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Watteau|editor-last=Ferr\u00e9|editor-first=Jean|editor-link=Jean Ferr\u00e9|publisher=\u00c9ditions Athena|year=1972|volume=3|location=Madrid|page=966}}</ref> Later studies have ruled possible doubts out, given the work's high artistic qualities as well as preparatory drawings and Thomassin's engraving; in her 1964 monograph, Nemilvova presumed Wrangel have been led to his conclusion because of the work's presence in the Gatchina Palace;{{sfnm|Nemilova|1964|1pp=28\u201329, 181|Nemilova|1982|2p=133|3a1=Grasselli|3a2=Rosenberg|3a3=Parmantier|3y=1984|3pp=311\u2013312}} in an entry for ''A Watteau Abecedario'', [[Martin Eidelberg]] adds that Mercier could not paint with the same characteristics and artistic level Watteau had, but also reveals that Wrangel pointed out supposed differences between the Hermitage painting and Thomassin\u2019s engraving: the blond actress lacks the coiffure seen in the engraving, there are also differences in the actor at the right.{{sfn|Eidelberg|2019}}\n\nScholars were also divided over the dating of ''Actors \u2026''. Adhemar presumed the work has been completed within a period from Spring to Autumn of 1716.{{sfn|Adhemar|1950|loc=cat. no. 154|p=119}} Similarly, [[Charles Sterling]]{{sfn|Sterling|1958|p=41}} had suggested a 1716\u20131717 dating, whereas Donald Posner{{sfn|Posner|1984|p=290}} opted for a 1717 dating, and so did Giovanni Macchia and Ettore Montagni;{{efn|Co-authors of a 1968 catalogue of Watteau's work from the ''L'opera competa di...'' series, edited by {{Interlanguage link|Ettore Camesasca|pt}}; later editions in French and English, published in the early 1970's, have the catalogue's authorship credited to Camesasca.}}{{sfn|Camesasca|1971|loc=cat. no. 162|p=115}} in 1959, Mathey proposed a relatively early date of 1714.<ref name=\"Mathey 1959, p. 68\">{{cite book|last=Mathey|first=Jacques|title=Antoine Watteau. Peintures r\u00e9apparues inconnues ou n\u00e9glig\u00e9es par les historiens|location=Paris|publisher=F. de Nobele|year=1959|language=fr|page=68}}</ref> Regarding aforementioned datings as too late, Nemilova dated ''Actors \u2026'' within a period of 1711\u20131712,{{efn|Claims of Nemilova's other or changed datings, most notably by Macchia and Montagni ({{harvnb|Camesasca|1971|loc=cat. no. 162|p=115}}), are considered erroneous.{{sfnm|Nemilova|1985|1p=445|Zolotov|1985|2p=100}}}} based on similarities with ''Du bel \u00e2ge \u2026'', now a lost painting engraved by Jean Moyreau and dated 1712 by Adhemar; both works have characters depicted in half-length with similar compositional rhythm and visual features.{{sfnm|Nemilova|1964|1p=182|Nemilova|1970|2p=156|Nemilova|1985|3p=445}} Others authors, such as [[Pierre Rosenberg]],{{sfn|Grasselli|Rosenberg|Parmantier|1984|p=312}} Marianne Roland Michel,{{sfn|Roland Michel|1984|p=217}} and Mary Vidal,<ref>\n{{Cite book|title=Watteau's Painted Conversations: Art, Literature, and Talk in Seventeenth- and Eighteenth-Century France|last=Vidal|first=Mary|publisher=Yale University Press|year=1992|isbn=0-300-05480-7|location=New Haven, London|page=146|postscript=. Ill. 142}}</ref> proposed a 1714-1715 dating; Roland Michel, while accepting identities suggested by Nemilova, objected her dating as too early and not taking into account the psychological study of subjects.{{sfn|Roland Michel|1984|p=217}}\n<!--\n==Provenance==\nIn an article published in the March 1928 issue of ''[[Gazette des Beaux-Arts]]'', Ernst reported that In years following Watteau's death, ''Actors...'' were owned by the royal collections conservator Nicolas Bailly, from which it passed to Pierre Crozat and his successors before 1755.{{rp|172\u2013173}} In 1772, it was acquired by [[Catherine II of Russia]], and was placed in the [[Winter Palace]]. At some point after the 1850s, it was relocated into the [[Gatchina Palace]]. In 1920, it was transitioned into the Winter Palace again, becoming an exhibit of the Hermitage's expositions.{{sfn|Nemilova|1964|pp=28-29, 182}}\n-->\n\n== Exhibition history ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ List of major exhibitions featuring the work\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Location\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Cat. no.\n! colspan=\"2\" |References\n|-\n!Primary\n!Secondary\n|-\n|1908\n| ''Les anciennes \u00e9coles de peinture dans les palais et collections priv\u00e9es russes'', by the {{Interlanguage link|Starye gody|lt=''Starye gody''|ru|\u0421\u0442\u0430\u0440\u044b\u0435 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u044b}} magazine\n|[[Imperial Society for the Encouragement of the Arts]], Saint Petersburg\n|286\n|<ref name=\"Benois\" />\n| rowspan=\"9\" |{{sfnm|1a1=Grasselli|1a2=Rosenberg|1a3=Parmantier|1y=1984|1p=313|Nemilova|1985|2p=445|Eidelberg|2019}}\n|-\n|1922\u20131925\n|Temporary exhibition of new acqusition from French painting of the 17th and 18th centuries\n|Hermitage Museum, Petrograd (later Leningrad)\n|*\n|<ref name=\"Ersnt\" /><ref name=Miller>{{cite magazine|last=Miller|first=V. F.|title=\u0424\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0443\u0437\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0436\u0438\u0432\u043e\u043f\u0438\u0441\u044c XVII-\u0433\u043e \u0438 XVIII-\u0433\u043e \u0432.\u0432. \u0432 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u0437\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0445 \u042d\u0440\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0436\u0430|work=\u0413\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434|language=ru|year=1923|issue=1|page=59}}</ref>\n|-\n|1955\n|''An Exhibition of French Art of the 15th-20th Centuries''\n|[[Pushkin Museum]], [[Moscow]]\n|*\n|<ref>{{Cite book|title=\u0412\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430 \u0444\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0443\u0437\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0438\u0441\u043a\u0443\u0441\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 XV-XX \u0432\u0432. \u041a\u0430\u0442\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433|last=Antonova|first=I. A.|last2=Berezina|first2=V. N.|last3=Borovaya|first3=T. A.|others=With introduction by {{Interlanguage link|Valeriy Prokofiev|lt=V. Prokofiev|ru|\u041f\u0440\u043e\u043a\u043e\u0444\u044c\u0435\u0432, \u0412\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0439 \u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}}|year=1955|location=Moscow|publisher=Iskusstvo|page=24|language=ru|display-authors=etal|author-link=Irina Antonova}}</ref>\n|-\n|1956\n|''An Exhibition of French Art of the 12th-20th Centuries''\n|Hermitage Museum, Leningrad\n|*\n|<ref>{{Cite book|title=\u0412\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430 \u0444\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0443\u0437\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0438\u0441\u043a\u0443\u0441\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 XII-XX \u0432\u0432. (1956; \u041b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0434). \u041a\u0430\u0442\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433|last=The Hermitage Museum, Leningrad|publisher=Iskusstvo|year=1956|location=Moscow|page=12|language=ru}}</ref>\n|-\n|1965\n|''Chefs-d'oeuvre de la peinture fran\u00e7aise dans les musees de l'Ermitage et de Moscou''\n|[[Mus\u00e9e des Beaux-Arts de Bordeaux]], [[Bordeaux]]\n|43\n|<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Charensol|first=Georges|date=June 15, 1965|title=Les mus\u00e9es de Russie a Bordeaux|journal=Revue des Deux Mondes|language=fr|pages=607\u2013613|jstor=44590025}}</ref>{{rp|611}}\n|-\n|1965\u20131966\n|''Chefs-d'oeuvre de la peinture fran\u00e7aise dans les musees de l'Ermitage et de Moscou''\n|[[Louvre]], Paris\n|41\n|<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Charensol|first=Georges|date=October 15, 1965|title=L'Ermitage au Louvre|journal=Revue des Deux Mondes|language=fr|pages=610\u2013616|jstor=44591522}}</ref>{{rp|614}}\n|-\n|1972\n|''Watteau and His Time''\n|Hermitage Museum, Leningrad\n|5\n|<ref>{{cite book|title=\u0412\u0430\u0442\u0442\u043e \u0438 \u0435\u0433\u043e \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u044f|author=Hermitage Museum, Leningrad|year=1972|location=Leningrad|publisher=Avrora|pages=12, 21|oclc=990348938}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Cailleux|first=Jean|date=October 1972|title='Watteau and his times' at the Hermitage|journal=[[The Burlington Magazine]]|volume=114|issue=835|pages=733\u2013734|jstor=877114}}</ref>{{rp|734}}\n|-\n|1980\n|''Les arts du th\u00e9\u00e2tre de Watteau \u00e0 Fragonard''\n|Galerie des Beaux-Arts, Mus\u00e9e des Beaux-Arts de Bordeaux, Bordeaux\n|67\n|<ref>{{Cite book|title=Les Arts du th\u00e9\u00e2tre de Watteau \u00e0 Fragonard|publisher=La Galerie|year=1980|location=Bordeaux|page=110|language=fr|oclc=606308317}}</ref>\n|-\n|1984\u20131985\n|''Watteau 1684\u20131721''\n|[[National Gallery of Art]], [[Washington, D.C.]]; [[Galeries nationales du Grand Palais]], Paris; [[Charlottenburg Palace]], [[Berlin]]\n|P. 29\n|<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Opperman|first=Hal|date=June 1988|title=''Watteau 1684-1721'' by Margaret Morgan Grasselli, Pierre Rosenberg and Nicole Parmentier|journal=The Art Bulletin|volume=70|issue=2|pages=354\u2013359|jstor=3051127}}</ref>{{rp|359}}\n|-class=\"sortbottom\"\n|colspan=10 style=font-size:8pt; align=center|\"'''*'''\" denotes an unnumbered entry.\n|}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Bibliography ==\n{{refbegin|2|indent=yes}}\n* {{Cite book|title=Watteau; sa vie, son oeuvre.|last=Adhemar|first=Helene|others=Includes \"L\u2019univers de Watteau\", an introduction by [[Ren\u00e9 Huyghe]]|publisher=P. Tisn\u00e9|year=1950|language=fr|location=Paris|oclc=853537|ref=harv|lastauthoramp=y}}\n* {{cite book|last=Belova|first=Y. N.|chapter=\u0410\u0442\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0431\u0443\u0446\u0438\u044f \u0438\u0437\u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043b\u0438\u0446 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0435 \u0410\u043d\u0442\u0443\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u0430\u0442\u0442\u043e \"\u0410\u043a\u0442\u0451\u0440\u044b \u0444\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0443\u0437\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0435\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0430\" [\"Attribution of persons portrayed by Antoine Watteau in his \"Actors of Theatre French\"]|title=\u042d\u043a\u0441\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0438\u0437\u0430 \u0438 \u0430\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0431\u0443\u0446\u0438\u044f \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0437\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0438\u0437\u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0438\u0441\u043a\u0443\u0441\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430: \u043c\u0430\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044b X \u043d\u0430\u0443\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0444\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0446\u0438\u0438|trans-title=Expertise and Attribution of Works of Fine Arts: Materials from the 10th Academic Conference|language=ru|location=Moscow|publisher=Magnum Ars|year=2006|pages=58\u201363|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|editor-first=Ettore|editor-last=Camesasca|url=https://archive.org/details/completepainting0000watt/page/115|url-access=registration|title=The Complete Paintings of Watteau|series=Classics of the World's Great Art|year=1971|location=New York|publisher=Harry N. Abrams|ref=harv|others=Introduction by John Sunderland|isbn=0810955253|page=[https://archive.org/details/completepainting0000watt/page/115 115]|oclc=143069|via=the [[Internet Archive]]}}\n* {{cite book|title=\u0410\u043d\u0442\u0443\u0430\u043d \u0412\u0430\u0442\u0442\u043e|trans-title=Antoine Watteau|language=ru|last=German|first