 topics}}\n}}\n\n[[Category:Pangasinan| ]]\n[[Category:Provinces of the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Luzon]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1611]]\n[[Category:1611 establishments in the Philippines]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the province in the Philippines}}\n{{pp-move-indef}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Pangasinan\n| official_name           = Province of Pangasinan<ref>({{lang-pag|Luyag na Pangasinan}}; {{lang-tl|Lalawigan ng Pangasinan}}; {{lang-ilo|Probinsia ti Pangasinan}})</ref>\n| settlement_type         = {{PH wikidata|settlement_type}}\n| image_skyline           = File:Pangasinan_Capitol_-_side_view_(Lingayen,_Pangasinan)(2018-02-25).jpg\n| image_caption           = Pangasinan Provincial Capitol in Lingayen\n| image_flag              = {{PH wikidata|image_flag}}\n| flag_size               = 120x80px\n| image_seal              = {{PH wikidata|image_seal}}\n| seal_size               = 120x80px\n| image_map               = {{PH wikidata|image_map}}\n| anthem                  = ''Luyag Ko Tan Yaman''\n| etymology               = ''Pang-asin-an'', lit. ''Place where salt is made''\n| map_caption             = Location in the Philippines\n| coordinates             = {{PH wikidata|coordinates}}\n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = {{PH wikidata|country}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[Regions of the Philippines|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1       = {{PH wikidata|region}}\n| established_title       = Founded\n| established_date        = April 5, 1580\n| seat_type               = Capital\n| seat                    = {{PH wikidata|seat}}\n| government_type         = {{PH wikidata|government_type}}\n| leader_party            = \n| leader_title            = [[Governor]]\n| leader_name             = Amado I. Espino III\n| leader_title1           = [[Vice Governor]]\n| leader_name1            = Mark Ronald D. Lambino\n| area_footnotes          = <ref name=nscblist>{{cite web |